(10, 'Antigua and Barbuda', 'ATG', 'ag.png', '<p>Want to earn your degree in warmer weather? &nbsp;I&rsquo;ll show you step-by-step below how to get a student visa for Antigua &amp; Barbuda.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Go to my&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.visahunter.com/visa/antigua-and-barbuda/\" title=\"Antigua and Barbuda Visa\">Antigua and Barbuda&nbsp;visa</a>&nbsp;page for information on how to get a different type of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.visahunter.com/visa/antigua-and-barbuda/\" title=\"Antigua and Barbuda Visa\">visa for Antigua and Barbuda</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Find your consulate</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>First, find out&nbsp;</strong>which consulate is responsible for visas where you live<strong>. &nbsp;This is where you will apply for your visa.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>If you&rsquo;re inside the U.S.:</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;Embassy of Antigua and Barbuda, Washington DC<br />\r\n32 New Mexico Avenue N.W.<br />\r\nWashington DC 20016</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>If you&rsquo;re outside of the U.S.:</strong>&nbsp;Find your consulate&nbsp;<a href=\"http://embassy.goabroad.com/embassies-of/antigua-barbuda\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Foreign consulate\">here</a>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>2</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Gather Documentation</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Next, gather the required documents.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>3</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Visa fees</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Visa Fee</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Check the website of the embassy or consulate you found above for the latest visa fee.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>4</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Submit documents</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Submit your documents and fees to your consulate found in Step 1.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>If applying by mail, please enclose a prepaid air bill, courier account number or SASE so you can get your passport returned to you. Very important!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>5</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Receive your visa</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Congratulations!&nbsp;</strong>The Antigua &amp; Barbuda Consulate General will<strong>&nbsp;give&nbsp;</strong>to you your brand new Antigua &amp; Barbuda visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>6</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Vaccination Requirements</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Don&rsquo;t get sick on your trip! Check&nbsp;</strong>vaccination requirements&nbsp;<a href=\"http://wwwnc.cdc.gov/travel/destinations/antigua-and-barbuda.htm\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Vaccination requirements\">here</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Further Reading</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Want Professional Visa Help?</strong>&nbsp;If you are a U.S. citizen and want professional help with getting a visa, check out my post on the&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"https://www.visahunter.com/articles/the-best-travel-visa-services-in-the-united-states/\" title=\"7 Best Travel Visa Services in the United States\">4 Best Travel Visa Services in the United States</a>.</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Worldwide Moving Guide:</strong>&nbsp;Everything you need to know in order to&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"https://www.visahunter.com/plan-your-move-abroad/\" title=\"Find Jobs\">plan your move</a></strong>&nbsp;to 65+ countries around the world.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Find an Embassy or Consulate:</strong>&nbsp;Check my&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"https://www.visahunter.com/embassy-and-consulate-finder/\" title=\"Embassy and Consulate Finder\">Worldwide Embassy and Consulate Finder</a></strong>&nbsp;to find the diplomatic representation nearest you.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Worldwide Jobs Guide:</strong>&nbsp;Be sure to check out my posts on&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"https://www.visahunter.com/articles/#makemoney\" title=\"Find Jobs\">how to find jobs</a></strong>&nbsp;in any country in the world.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Worldwide Dating Guide:</strong>&nbsp;Also, check out my posts on&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"https://www.visahunter.com/articles/#datingandromance\" title=\"Find Jobs\">the best online dating sites</a></strong>&nbsp;in 60+ countries around the world.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-15', 1),
(11, 'Argentina', 'ARG', 'ar.png', '<p><a href=\"https://www.iesabroad.org/student-visa/argentina#citizenship\">Do You Need a Visa?</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.iesabroad.org/student-visa/argentina#applying\">Applying for a Visa for Argentina</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>You&#39;re so close to being in Argentina. Can you almost smell the chimichurri? Have you read reviews on all the best asado&nbsp;spots? Before you can dive into your foodie adventures, let&#39;s make sure you can enter and stay in Argentina officially.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Every year our team of visa specialists support each of our students&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.iesabroad.org/argentina\" target=\"_blank\">studying abroad in Argentina</a>&nbsp;to have the proper documents to enter and stay in the country. Let&#39;s get started!</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Argentine visa requirements are determined by the Argentine government, not by IES Abroad. While our team of visa specialists regularly updates this page, the most up-to-date and official information can be found on Argentina government and consulate websites. This page was last updated December 9, 2019.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Do You Need a Visa for Argentina?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Depending on your IES Abroad program and citizenship, you may need a student visa to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.iesabroad.org/argentina\">study abroad in Argentina</a>. We&rsquo;ve outlined citizenship options below to help you learn more about your requirements for legal entry and stay in Argentina.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>If you will be going on a&nbsp;Customized &amp; Faculty-Led Program, you may need a student visa depending on the length and nature of your program. Learn more in your&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.iesabroad.org/myiesabroad\">myIESabroad</a>&nbsp;account.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Applying for a Visa for Argentina</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Once you are accepted to your semester or year-long IES Abroad program, you will find detailed instructions to apply for an Argentine student visa&nbsp;in your&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.iesabroad.org/myiesabroad\">myIESabroad</a>&nbsp;account. For now, read below to get an idea of what the process will look like.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are a non-U.S. citizen, refer to the visa information in your&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.iesabroad.org/myiesabroad\">myIESabroad</a>&nbsp;account to determine whether or not you need a visa and what the process will be to apply. Contact your&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.iesabroad.org/study-abroad/contact/your-advisor\">IES Abroad Advisor</a>&nbsp;with further questions.</p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-15', 0),
(12, 'Armenia', 'ARM', 'am.png', '<h1>Study Visa for Armenia</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>Students who wish to enter the Republic of Armenia must have a tourist visa. Students holding this visa can apply to the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://armeniaeducation.info/higher-education/higher-education-institutions-and-qualifications.html\" target=\"_blank\">higher education institutions</a>&nbsp;of their choice in Armenia. Once you get admission to the institution, the particular institution will apply to the consular section of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs (MFA) for entry permission for you. After getting the entry permission from the MFA, students must apply for a visa in the Armenian embassy nearest to them. The Embassy issues a single entry visa for which the student has to pay the charges in the embassy itself. Once a student is in Armenia, he/she gets a resident card, free of costs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>International students must have valid passport, entry visa or a document of residency status.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Contact your nearest&nbsp;<a href=\"https://armeniaeducation.info/international-students/list-of-armenia-embassies-and-consulate-worldwide.html\" target=\"_blank\">Armenia embassy</a>&nbsp;or consulate for detailed information about visa application procedure and documentation.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Types of Visas for Armenia</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Visitor (tourist) visa:</strong>&nbsp;A tourist/visitor visa is for foreigners who wish to come to Armenia for business, tourism, medical treatment, seeing relatives and friends, etc. This visa is valid for a period of 1 year, and issued for one time entry or for multiple entries.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Official visa:</strong>&nbsp;The official visa is for individuals who possess a service or official passport.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Single entry visa or multiple entries visa: These are issued to international functionaries who come to the Republic of Armenia after receiving an invite from foreign diplomatic representations or&nbsp;Armenian officials&nbsp;or international establishments. These are valid for a period of 1 year.</li>\r\n	<li>Multiple entries visas are also issued to non-diplomatic individuals working as foreign representatives. It is also issued to their families, and international establishments. Such visas are valid for a period of 3 years.</li>\r\n	<li>Single entry visa or multiple entries visas are also issued to the official representatives having ordinary passport. These are valid for 1 year.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Diplomatic visa:</strong>&nbsp;This visa is for individuals with diplomatic status or for individuals who hold a diplomatic passport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Multiple entries visa is issued for a period of 3 years; single entry visa or multiple entries visa is issued for a period of 1 year to official representatives and their families; and single entry visa for entry into the country for non-official reasons is issued for a period of 120 days.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Transit visa:</strong>&nbsp;A transit visa is issued for single entry or for multiple entries. This visa is issued for stay in the Republic of Armenia for a maximum duration of 3-4 days and is valid for a period of 1 year.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Visa Conditions</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3><em>Who Requires a Visa to Travel to Armenia?</em></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Citizens of some countries are&nbsp;<strong>unilaterally exempted</strong>&nbsp;from the requirement of getting a visa for Armenia. Click&nbsp;<a href=\"http://mfa.am/u_files/file/consulate/visa/visafreelisteng2.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>&nbsp;to know about those countries.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are certain countries with which Armenia has a&nbsp;<strong>visa-free system</strong>&nbsp;as per the bilateral and multilateral agreements. To get the details of such countries, click&nbsp;<a href=\"http://mfa.am/u_files/file/consulate/visa/whoneedsvisa_eng1.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Holders of&nbsp;<strong>all other</strong>&nbsp;national passports and travel documents are required to get a entry visa for Armenia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Nationals of foreign countries for whom a visa-free regime is established can stay in Armenia for not more than 180 days during 1 year.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Invitation based visa:</em>&nbsp;Some of the countries citizens require invitation in order to apply for visitor visa for Armenia. To get the list of such countries, click&nbsp;<a href=\"http://mfa.am/u_files/file/consulate/visa/invitation_only_eng.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Visa Application Procedure</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>International students must apply for study visa at their nearest Armenia embassy. To apply they must first be accepted by the higher education institution in Armenia. Fill out a visa application form and submit it along with the required documents.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Documentation</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Following documents are required:</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Visa application form:</strong>&nbsp;It must be completely filled and signed</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A valid<strong>&nbsp;travel document:</strong>&nbsp;Passport</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Three passport sized&nbsp;<strong>photos</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Invitation</strong>&nbsp;(if required)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Cover letter:</strong>&nbsp;It should include the purpose and duration of stay in Armenia</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Admission letter</strong>&nbsp;from the Armenian educational institution</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Tuition fee receipt</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Educational credentials:</strong>&nbsp;Certificates, degrees and mark sheets; secondary education graduation certificate or&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>university certificates.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>English language proficiency proof:&nbsp;</strong>TOEFL / IELTS score certificates</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Accommodation proof:</strong>&nbsp;Can be rent agreement or letter from institution (if taken university accommodation)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Evidence of&nbsp;<strong>financial means</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Evidence of a&nbsp;<strong>valid health insurance</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>**All the documents mentioned above must be translated in English Language.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Visa Fees</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The visa fee varies. To know about the visa fee, visit the official website of&nbsp;<a href=\"http://mfa.am/en/visa/\" target=\"_blank\">Ministry of Foreign Affairs, Armenia</a>.</p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-15', 0),
(13, 'Aruba', 'ABW', 'aw.png', '<p>When you have applied to study at the University of Aruba, we will help you to apply for a student visa at DIMAS (immigration authority).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The visa application procedure in short:</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Apply to the University</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Once the Office of Student Affairs receives your application and all necessary documents, a student file will be created. This file will be sent to the Dean of the faculty to which you have applied. Once the Office of Student Affairs receives approval, you will be informed by e-mail.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Once accepted, you need the following forms for DIMAS:</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>1. Proof of Finance</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Study loan and/or confirmation of parents.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>2. Copy of Medical and Travel insurance</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>The statement about your insurance should be in English, Spanish or Dutch and should cover medical expenses and travel insurance in Aruba.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>3. Filed out DIMAS forms</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Go to&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.dimasaruba.com/\">www.dimasaruba.com</a>. The website is in Dutch but you can translate the site to English or Spanish with the Translate button on the right side of the page.&nbsp; Go to Download Forms &gt; Forms and lists of Requirements &gt; Permits.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Please fill out the Student application form and lists (Student_EA.pdf):&nbsp;<a href=\"http://translate.google.com/translate?client=tmpg&amp;hl=en&amp;langpair=nl|en&amp;u=http%3A//www.dimasaruba.aw/\">http://translate.google.com/translate?client=tmpg&amp;hl=en&amp;langpair=nl|en&amp;u=http%3A//www.dimasaruba.aw/</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h4>4. Original paper of good conduct</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>A certificate of good conduct can be obtained in your own country. DIMAS will need an original certificate, not older than 1 year.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>5. Four identical ID photos</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>The photos need to be in colour and conform to passport/ID standards.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>6. Official proof of payment</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Proof of payment of fees with description: RBC bank account# 30.58.646, ref OSA Exchange Student. The total fee is $200 ($92 for DIMAS, $88 for a medical test which should be taken within 10 days after arrival and $20 for administration costs, government stamp and promotional items).</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>&nbsp;7. Copy of return ticket</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>A copy of the return ticket that you booked.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You need to take all these forms with you to Aruba to apply for your visa at the DIMAS office.</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:20px\"><em>&nbsp;for more information </em></span>:https://www.ua.aw/international/visa/</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-16', 0),
(14, 'Australia', 'AUS', 'au.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>How to apply Australia for Student Visa From Bangladesh</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">You&#39;ll need the Student visa (subclass 500) to study in Australia. This visa is made specifically for students like you who are ready to begin their study abroad adventure in Australia. Find out the best information about the process of getting the Student visa (subclass 500) to decide if studying abroad in Australia is right for you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>&nbsp;Cost of a Student Visa in Australia:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">The current fees in order to apply for a Student Visa&nbsp;are set to $575 AUD.&nbsp;The price is always the same no matter the length of your studies.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Please note that this price may vary depending on the location where you apply for your Student Visa (Australia or onshore). The Department of Immigration and Border Protection has built a pricing estimator tool to help future applicants to quickly get a price overview of their visa application.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>In order to apply for a Student Visa, you will need to meet the following requirements.</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Confirmation Of Enrolment (COE)</li>\r\n	<li>Genuine Temporary Entrant (GTE)</li>\r\n	<li>Financial requirements</li>\r\n	<li>English Proficiency Requirement</li>\r\n	<li>Australian Health Requirement</li>\r\n	<li>Australian Character Requirement</li>\r\n	<li>Overseas Student Health Cover (OSHC)</li>\r\n	<li>Cost of annual living amounts</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Renewal of the Student Visa in Australia</strong><br />\r\nYou can renew your Student Visa as many times as you want, as long as you are enrolled in a course approved by CRICOS. However, you need to be advised that if you have had multiple student visas in the past, the Government may question the genuineness of your application.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Our expert staff at Go Study can explain all your options relating to extending or renewing your student visa.</p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2018-10-15', 1),
(15, 'Austria', 'AUT', 'at.png', '<p><strong>Study In Austria From Bangladesh:</strong></p>\n\n<p>Study Hotel Mgr. in AUSTRIA(schengen country),Study Hotel &amp; Tourism Management in AUSTRIA.<br />\nHeart of Europe.</p>\n\n<p><br />\n<strong>Surrounded by:</strong><br />\nGermany,Switzerland,Italy,Hungary,Slovakia,<br />\nSlovenia,Czech Republic &amp; Lichtenstein.</p>\n\n<p>Programs offered: Diploma(2 years in-<br />\n-Hospitality &amp; Tourism Management<br />\n-Event &amp; Banquet Management<br />\n- Wellness &amp; Spa Management.</p>\n\n<p> Eligibility : HSC with IELTS (not mandatory but a skype interview is required.</p>\n\n<p> Course fee : Euro4500x2= &euro; 9000 for Year 1.<br />\nOther fees: Registration fee &euro;1400+Books &amp; lesson material &euro;141.<br />\nBefore visa student have to remit &euro;11,810.<br />\nDocuments required for Offer letter :</p>\n\n<p>Send the ITM College application form together with the following documents by e-mail to office@itm-college.eu or mail it to ITM College, Johann Strauss Stra&szlig;e 2, 2540 Bad V&ouml;slau, Austria:<br />\n- Apply in prescribed Application form<br />\n- High school diploma</p>\n\n<p>- Birth certificate</p>\n\n<p>- Curriculum vitae</p>\n\n<p>- Motivation letter (300-500 words)</p>\n\n<p>- Copy of passport</p>\n\n<p>- 2 passport photos</p>\n\n<p>All official documents need to be submitted with a certified English or German translation.<br />\nUpon receipt of the complete set of application documents you will be invited to an skype interview. This can be in person or via Skype.</p>\n\n<p>Documents required for Offer letter :<br />\nThe following documents have to be submitted at VFS- Austrian Embassy,Dhaka::</p>\n\n<p>- The properly completed visa application form<br />\n- A of passport</p>\n\n<p>- Birth certificate</p>\n\n<p>- Passport photo</p>\n\n<p>- Housing confirmation</p>\n\n<p>- Confirmation of the health insurance</p>\n\n<p>- Extract of criminal records</p>\n\n<p>- Of savings account</p>\n\n<p>- Study confirmation</p>\n\n<p><br />\nPlease be aware that the processing of your visa application may require up to 15 days.</p>\n\n<p>Refund &amp; Handling fee: In case the visa application is turned down by the embassy, ITM College will return the full amount deducted by an EUR 500,00 handling fee.<br />\nPlease visit our office, know details &amp; take decision.</p>\n\n<p>Study Aircraft Maintenance Engineering with Scholarship &amp; ob of Job of US$3,000 er anum.</p>\n\n<p>We can also arrange admission in other countries of Europe like Sweden, Denmark,<br />\nLithuania, Hungary, Malta, Greece,China and Russia(no remittance of Tuition fee before visa).</p>\n\n<p>Contact: 01958-666900 &amp; 01958-666999</p>\n', '2018-09-11', '2018-12-22', 1),
(16, 'Azerbaijan', 'AZE', 'az.png', '<p><strong>Student Visa in Azerbaijan from Bangladesh:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Study Hotel Management in French Institute at Baku,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>capital of Azerbaijan and work part-time(to earn 200~300 per month).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1 week Theory + 1 week Practice at an International Hotel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Paid Internship Opportunities in Europe in the 2nd Year.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> Students can study 3rd year in European campus or 35 campuses in world..</p>\r\n\r\n<p>International Curriculum based on European Hospitality Management Standards.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Internationally-Recognized French Diploma .</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Part time job opportunity to earn 200~300 per month</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Package cost : BDTk 5(five lac).Payment after visa.<br />\r\nPackage includes : Application fee of &euro;200 + One year Tuition fee of &euro;4000+<br />\r\nAdmission &amp; visa processing + service charge<br />\r\nEligibility : Min. HSC pass. Good in English .A skype interview is required.<br />\r\nProcedure:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. Apply with all original Educational document + Passport + Photo + Initial deposit of Tk20,000,<br />\r\n2. Skype interview. If accepted,visa processing will start.<br />\r\n3. If not accepted by French school,Tk 19,000 will be refunded.<br />\r\n4. After visa approval, student have pay balance amount of package cost and cooperate with us to make bank draft of Tuition fee. This bank drft will be with us till student reach safely in Baku.<br />\r\n5. Student will buy air ticket and fly with our letter along with photo copy of Bank draft.<br />\r\n6. We&rsquo;ll send bank draft to Hotel Institute by courier after the reaching at Baku.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We can also arrange admission in other countries of Europe like Poland,Hungary,Lithuania, ,Netherlands,<br />\r\nDenmark,Italy, France,Switzerland.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>CHINA with full scholarship &amp; stipend for studying MBBS,Engineering,Management<br />\r\n,Forestry,Aronautical,Marine etc.</p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2018-12-22', 1),
(17, 'Bahamas', 'BHS', 'bs.png', '<p>A Student Visa in the Bahamas allows a foreign national the opportunity to immigrate to Bahamas on a temporary basis in order to undertake a course of study in the nation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Studying in the Bahamas is an increasingly popular choice for undergraduates across the world; Bahamas offers a long history of quality in learning with a host of educational establishments.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Immigration to Bahamas has grown significantly in the last decade owing to the comparatively liberal immigration policy coupled with the high quality of life which can be obtained in the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A Study visa allows the holders to live and work in the Bahamas for as long as they need to complete their course in order to help support themselves and any dependents.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Visa Eligibility</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The following criteria must be met.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; A letter of acceptance must be provided demonstrating that an applicant has been offered a place on a full time course of study at a recognised educational institution.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Candidates must be able to demonstrate evidence of enough funds to support themselves in the country.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; It must be shown that the course fees have been paid in full.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Private medical insurance must be arranged and documentary evidence of this must be provided.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; It must be the candidate&#39;s demonstrable intention to return to their own country at the end of their period of study.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>To study in any one of the universities in Bahamas, international students must get a Bahamian student visa depending on their country of origin.&nbsp;<strong>RocApply</strong>&nbsp;has made it easy for you to follow what documentation may be needed upon visa application on this guide!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It is, however, advised to always check with the consulate/embassy for more details on visa requirements.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To receive a Bahamian Student Visa, you must first get accepted into an educational institution in Bahamas. This is why it is important to apply through&nbsp;<strong>RocApply</strong>&nbsp;and secure a vacancy in any of the universities of your choice to proceed with an application for a visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The student then has to apply at the Ministry of Foreign Affairs for authorization for your Student Visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;if you need mor information : https://www.rocapply.com/study-in-bahamas/about-bahamas/bahamas-visa-requirements.html</p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-16', 0);
