(71, 'Ethiopia', 'ETH', 'et.png', '<h1>Ethiopia Visa for Bangladeshi Citizens</h1>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://application.ethiopiaonlinevisa.com/application/?option=BD\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Apply for eVisa</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.ethiopiaonlinevisa.com/\" title=\"Ethiopia eVisa\">Ethiopia electronic visa</a>&nbsp;for Bangladeshi citizens is a quick and easy procedure that can be completed online.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Although citizens from Kenya and Djibouti can enter Ethiopia without a visa, this document is mandatory for nationals of other countries from June 1, 2018.&nbsp;<strong>Bangladeshi passport holders</strong>&nbsp;must be aware that it is not possible to obtain an&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.ethiopiaonlinevisa.com/ethiopia-visa-on-arrival-complete-guide/\" title=\"Ethiopia Visa on Arrival\">Ethiopian visa on arrival</a>, therefore, a travel permit must be obtained online in the form of an eVisa.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Do Bangladeshi Travelers Need a Visa for Ethiopia?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Bangladeshi citizens must&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.ethiopiaonlinevisa.com/tourist-visa/\" title=\"Ethiopia Tourist Visa\">apply for a tourist visa before their arrival in Ethiopia</a>&nbsp;in order to avoid any inconvenience when reaching the border. The Ethiopian tourist visa has a validity of either&nbsp;<strong>30 days or 90 days</strong>&nbsp;depending on the type of visa requested at the moment of submitting the information on the application.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It must be pointed out that the visa is&nbsp;<strong>valid from the day of entry</strong>&nbsp;at the country and not from the date of issue.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Travelers must note that visa holders must enter Ethiopia via&nbsp;<strong>Addis Adaba Bole International Airport</strong>. No other port of entry is eligible for this type of visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bangladeshi travelers should also keep in mind that this visa is only valid for tourist purposes and business-related activities are not allowed with this document. For business trips,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.ethiopiaonlinevisa.com/business-visa/\" title=\"Ethiopian Business Visa\">an Ethiopian business application</a>&nbsp;will need to be made.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Documents Required to Obtain the Ethiopian Visa for Bangladeshis</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>In order to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.ethiopiaonlinevisa.com/application/\" title=\"Apply for Ethiopian Visa\">apply successfully for an eVisa for Ethiopia</a>, the Bangladeshi applicant must provide these documents:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Passport</strong>&nbsp;with a validity of at least 6 months from the date of entry in Ethiopia</li>\r\n	<li>A recent passport size&nbsp;<strong>photograph</strong></li>\r\n	<li>A valid&nbsp;<strong>email address</strong></li>\r\n	<li>A valid&nbsp;<strong>credit or debit card</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The following information must be provided as part of the application:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Personal information:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Full name (as shown on passport, including middle names if applicable)</li>\r\n	<li>Date of birth</li>\r\n	<li>Country of birth</li>\r\n	<li>City of birth</li>\r\n	<li>Country of citizenship</li>\r\n	<li>Gender</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Passport details:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Passport date of issue</li>\r\n	<li>Passport date of expiry</li>\r\n	<li>Passport number</li>\r\n	<li>Country of issue</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The applicant must make sure that the information submitted is&nbsp;<strong>accurate and complete</strong>&nbsp;as updating or changing details at a later stage might cause delays in obtaining the document. It is very important to check that the whole application is correct and all the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.ethiopiaonlinevisa.com/required-documents-travel-ethiopia/\" title=\"Required Documents for Ethiopia\">needed documents for the Ethiopia eVisa</a>&nbsp;are included and in order to avoid inconvenience at the immigration counter.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Travelers from Bangladesh with more than one nationality will need to&nbsp;<strong>choose one passport</strong>&nbsp;to fill out the application. There should be no inconsistencies between the travel document and the details entered for the eVisa application.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Additional requirements may apply,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.ethiopiaonlinevisa.com/vaccines-travel-ethiopia/\" title=\"Vaccinations for Ethiopia\"><strong>such as proof of yellow fever vaccination</strong></a>&nbsp;in case the applicant has been traveling to at-risk areas or transiting through an airport in one of these regions for more than 12 hours.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Bangladeshis Arriving in Ethiopia With an eVisa: Further Considerations</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Upon arrival at the airport, travelers will be requested the below items:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A printed copy of the eVisa</li>\r\n	<li>A photocopy of the passport</li>\r\n	<li>Their passport (with at least 6 months validity at the moment of entering the country)</li>\r\n	<li>At least two blank pages on the passport for stamps or notes from the immigration department</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Travelers are advised that the visa allows for a&nbsp;<strong>single entry</strong>, therefore, if citizens from Bangladesh leave the country and wish to enter Etiopia again, they will need to obtain a new eVisa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A&nbsp;<strong>visa extension</strong>&nbsp;for up to 30 days can be requested in person at the Head Office of The Main Department for Immigration and Nationality Affairs in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.ethiopiaonlinevisa.com/addis-ababa-capital-largest-city-ethiopia/\" title=\"Guide to Addis Ababa\">Addis Ababa</a>. Bangladeshi citizens need to still meet all the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.ethiopiaonlinevisa.com/extending-ethiopian-visa-overstaying/\" title=\"Extending an Ethiopian Visa\">Ethiopia online visa requirements when requesting the extension</a>&nbsp;and the final decision will be made by the local immigration authorities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bangladeshi visitors must be also aware that&nbsp;<strong>staying in Ethiopia beyond the validity of the visa</strong>&nbsp;might incur fines or legal penalties.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px\">fpr more information :&nbsp;https://www.ethiopiaonlinevisa.com/requirements/bangladeshi-citizens/</span></p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-18', 1),
(72, 'Falkland Islands', 'FLK', 'fk.png', '<p><span style=\"font-size:22px\">for all information plz click heare :&nbsp;https://www.visahq.com/bangladesh/requirements/falkland-islands/resident-iceland/</span></p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-18', 1),
(73, 'Faroe Islands', 'FRO', 'fo.png', '<h1>&nbsp;</h1>\r\n\r\n<h1>VISA</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>If you plan on making a short-term visit (up to&nbsp;90 days) to the Faroe Islands, you must have a visa that is valid for entry into the Faroe Islands, if you come from a country with a visa requirement.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A visa to enter Denmark or another Schengen country is&nbsp;<strong>not&nbsp;</strong>valid for entry into the Faroe Islands. The Faroe Islands is not a&nbsp;member&nbsp;of the EU and&nbsp;not a part&nbsp;to the Schengen Agreement.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIf you need a visa to enter the Faroe Islands, you will most likely also need a Schengen visa, since most travel to these two countries goes through a Schengen country, such as Denmark.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nCitizens from visa free countries do not need a visa.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<a href=\"http://www.nyidanmark.dk/en-us/coming_to_dk/visa/need_visa/who_needs_visa.htm\">Find out whether citizens of your country need a visa to enter the Schengen area.</a><br />\r\n<br />\r\nCitizens&nbsp;of&nbsp;<strong>Denmark</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>Finland</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>Iceland</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>Norway</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>Sweden</strong>&nbsp;are free to enter, reside, study and work on&nbsp;the Faroe Islands.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>CONDITIONS AND APPLICATION</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>In general, if you qualify for a Danish visa, you also qualify for a visa to enter the Faroe Islands. The application procedure for visas to enter the&nbsp;Faroe Islands is the same as for a Danish visa. If you are seeking to obtain a visa to enter the Faroe Islands, as well as a Schengen visa, you only need to submit a single application.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<a href=\"http://www.nyidanmark.dk/en-us/coming_to_dk/visa/how-to/how_to_app.htm\">Read more about&nbsp;applying for a visa</a><br />\r\n<br />\r\nVisas to enter the Faroe Islands are issued by Danish&nbsp;diplomatic missions&nbsp;abroad or the Danish Immigration Service.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>IMPORTANT EXCEPTIONS</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A Danish/Schengen visa does not give permission to enter the Faroe Islands.</li>\r\n	<li>Residence permits, residence cards and D visas, whether issued by Denmark or another Schengen country, do not give permission to enter the Faroe Islands.</li>\r\n	<li>An ID card issued by an EU or Schengen country that is valid for entry into Denmark does not give permission to enter the Faroe Islands. Such individuals will require a passport to travel to the Faroe Islands.</li>\r\n	<li>Individuals with a visa valid only for entry to the Faroe Islands are not required to possess travellers&rsquo; health insurance.<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>HOLDERS OF DANISH RESIDENCE&nbsp;PERMITS&nbsp;WHO REQUIRE A VISA TO ENTER THE FAROE ISLANDS</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>If you hold a Danish residence permit, but require a visa to enter the Faroe Islands, the Immigration Service or the police can issue an entry permit.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>IF YOU ENTERED DENMARK ON A VISA OR RESIDENCE PERMIT ISSUED BY ANOTHER SCHENGEN COUNTRY</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>You must apply for a visa to enter the Faroe Islands before you arrive in Denmark. In certain cases, the Immigration Service or the police can issue a permit if you are already in Denmark.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn such cases, you must declare the purpose of your visit to the Faroe Islands, possess a ticket or other documentation for the planned trip&nbsp; and state why you did not apply for a visa before entering Denmark.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>HOLDERS&nbsp;OF RESIDENCE PERMITS VALID FOR&nbsp;THE FAROE ISLANDS &nbsp;WHO NEED A VISA TO TRAVEL TO DENMARK</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>If you&nbsp;hold a residence permit valid for&nbsp;the Faroe Islands , you will need a visa to enter Denmark. Such individuals do not need supplementary travellers&rsquo; insurance in order to enter Denmark.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSuch individuals must also have a visa if they wish to travel to another Schengen country.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAn application for a visa to enter Denmark or a Schengen country&nbsp;must be submitted to the police on the Faroe Islands, who will then send it to the Immigration Service.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>EXTENSION</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>In certain cases, a visa giving you permission to enter the Faroe Islands&nbsp;can be extended beyond the 90-day validity period. Extensions can be granted to, among others, individuals visiting a spouse, partner, fianc&eacute;(e), boyfriend, girlfriend, child, parents or siblings, or in the event of serious illness. An application to extend your visa&nbsp;must be submitted to the police on the Faroe Islands, who will then send it to the Immigration Service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px\">for more information :&nbsp;https://www.studyinfaroeislands.fo/default.aspx</span></p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-18', 1),
(74, 'Fiji', 'FJI', 'fj.png', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://studee.imgix.net/images/guide/guides__how-to-apply-for-a-fiji-student-visa--hero.jpg?ixlib=js-2.3.2&amp;auto=format&amp;fit=crop&amp;q=45&amp;w=1920&amp;h=640%201920w\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h1>How to apply for a Fiji student visa</h1>\r\n\r\n<h2>In this guide:</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://studee.com/guides/how-to-apply-for-a-fiji-student-visa/#applicationsteps\">Application steps:</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://studee.com/guides/how-to-apply-for-a-fiji-student-visa/#requireddocuments\">Required documents:</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://studee.com/guides/how-to-apply-for-a-fiji-student-visa/#canyourfamilymembersjoinyou\">Can your family members join you?</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://studee.com/guides/how-to-apply-for-a-fiji-student-visa/#areyouallowedtoworkinfiji\">Are you allowed to work in Fiji?</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://studee.com/guides/how-to-apply-for-a-fiji-student-visa/#whatifyourapplicationisrejected\">What if your application is rejected?</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>If you&rsquo;re an international student who is hoping to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://studee.com/fiji/\">study abroad in Fiji</a>, you&rsquo;ll need to secure a study permit before setting off.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Fijian student permits are awarded for up to three years but can be extended depending on the length of your program. They cost FJD $133 ($63), but you&rsquo;ll also pay an issue fee of FJD $180 ($85).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It can take anywhere between three and 21 days to get your permit issued, so it&rsquo;s best not to leave your application to the last minute.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://studee.com/search-programs/?country=fiji\">Find programs in Fiji</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Application steps:</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Follow these steps when applying for a Fijian study permit:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><strong>Accept a university place:</strong>&nbsp;Receive a formal admissions letter from your chosen Fijian institution and pay any enrollment fees.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Download, print, and complete the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.fijihighcommission.org.uk/forms/2011/student_permit.pdf\">study permit application form</a>:</strong>&nbsp;You must fill out all sections of the form to have the best chance of application approval.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Gather supporting documentation:</strong>&nbsp;Alongside the visa application form, you&rsquo;ll need to submit several documents. You can find a full list of what you&rsquo;ll need in the section below.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Submit your application and pay fee:</strong>&nbsp;Visit a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.embassy-worldwide.com/country/fiji/#:~:text=There%20are%20about%2010%20Foreign,spread%20all%20over%20the%20world.\">Fijian embassy or consulate in your home country</a>&nbsp;to submit your application. If there&rsquo;s no embassy available in your country, you can post your documents to one of&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.immigration.gov.fj/travel-requirements/fiji-visas\">Fiji&rsquo;s visa processing offices</a>.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Await a decision:</strong>&nbsp;The Fijian Department of Immigration will notify you of your application outcome within a few weeks.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h2>Required documents:</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Failing to attach the correct documentation is a surefire way to get your application refused. The list below outlines everything you&rsquo;ll need to include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A completed&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.fijihighcommission.org.uk/forms/2011/student_permit.pdf\">study permit application form</a></li>\r\n	<li>A passport that&rsquo;s valid for at least three months after your program finishes</li>\r\n	<li>A copy of the biodata page of your passport</li>\r\n	<li>4 recent passport photos of yourself</li>\r\n	<li>The numbers and details of your arriving and departing flights</li>\r\n	<li>Proof that you have the financial means to support yourself during your studies</li>\r\n	<li>A copy of your birth certificate</li>\r\n	<li>Details of your address and living arrangements in Fiji</li>\r\n	<li>Formal admissions letter from your university</li>\r\n	<li>A medical report issued within the last three months</li>\r\n	<li>A certificate of police clearance from the authorities in your home country</li>\r\n	<li>Means to pay the application and issuance fees</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px\">for more information :&nbsp;https://studee.com/guides/how-to-apply-for-a-fiji-student-visa/</span></p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-18', 1),
(75, 'Finland', 'FIN', 'fi.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Study in Finland from Bangladesh:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">When it comes to top quality education, Finland is one of the first countries that comes to mind. Finland has succeeded in not only keeping up with educational progress, but also excelling at setting a global standard.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Finland has not opened their embassy in Bangladesh; Finnish embassy in Delhi is accredited to Bangladesh.<br />\r\nAddress: Embassy of Finland<br />\r\nE-3, Nyaya Marg, Chanakyapuri<br />\r\nNew Delhi 110021, India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Tel: +91 11 4149 7500<br />\r\nFax: +91 11 4149 7555<br />\r\nE-mail: sanomat.nde@formin.fi<br />\r\nVisa and residence permit:<br />\r\nTel. +91 11 4149 7570<br />\r\nFax: +91 11 4149 7550<br />\r\nE-mail: visa.nde@formin.fi<br />\r\nWeb page: www.finland.org.in</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Basic Requirements for Finland Visa:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">1. Letter of acceptance from the university<br />\r\n2. Visa application form, accompanied by one colour photograph<br />\r\n3. Passport or other travel document (the identification page)<br />\r\n4. Old passports of the applicant Bank statements of the applicant.<br />\r\n5. Flight Reservation<br />\r\n6. Proof of accommodation<br />\r\n7. Travel medical insurance<br />\r\n8. Cover letter from the applicant<br />\r\n9. No objection certificate (NOC) from employer<br />\r\n10. Under 18 years: No objection certificate (NOC) from both of the parents.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Visa Fee:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">EURO 60, BDT 6200/-<br />\r\nIndian VFS Service Charges &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\nINR 1560, BDT 2000/-</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><br />\r\n<strong>Processing time:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Visa and admission processing may take upto 80 to 90 working days (Time may vary case to case)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Call for more information:</strong><br />\r\n<span style=\"background-color:#f5f5f5; color:#333333; font-family:&quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14px\">01958-666999 &amp; 01958-666900</span></p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2018-12-22', 1),
(76, 'France', 'FRA', 'fr.png', '<h1>How To Get A Student Visa For France</h1>\r\n\r\n<p><iframe frameborder=\"0\" height=\"90\" id=\"google_ads_iframe_/8070/Topuni-Web/student-info/studying-abroad/how-get-student-visa-france_1\" name=\"google_ads_iframe_/8070/Topuni-Web/student-info/studying-abroad/how-get-student-visa-france_1\" scrolling=\"no\" title=\"3rd party ad content\" width=\"728\"></iframe></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Do you need a French student visa?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Whether or not you require a&nbsp;<strong>student visa for France</strong>&nbsp;will depend on whether or not you are an EU national.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you&nbsp;<em>are</em>&nbsp;an EU national, or national from the EEA, Switzerland, Norway, Iceland or Liechtenstein, you do not require a&nbsp;<strong>French student visa</strong>. Instead, all you will need in order to legally&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.topuniversities.com/where-to-study/europe/france/guide\">study in France</a>&nbsp;is a valid passport or other valid travel ID.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are a national from anywhere else in the world, you will need to obtain a student visa for France in order to be able to undertake study.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What type of French student visa will you need?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.topuniversities.com/sites/default/files/Schengen%20student%20visa.jpg\" style=\"height:199px; width:300px\" title=\"\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are several types of French student visa, and the one you require will differ depending on how long you are planning to study in France for.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Schengen student visa (short-stay)</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>If your studies will last less than three months, and you are sure you will not be spending any longer in the country, then you should apply for the&nbsp;<em>court s&eacute;jour pour &eacute;tude,</em>&nbsp;otherwise known as the short-stay or Schengen student visa. The Schengen student visa is issued free of charge and cannot be renewed.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Visa to sit entrance exams</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>If you need to travel to France in order to sit one or more university entrance exams, you can apply for the&nbsp;<em>visa de court s&eacute;jour &eacute;tudiant concours</em>, which simply means a visa for sitting entrance exams. If you sit your exam and pass, you are then eligible to apply for a renewable, one-year residence permit. For more information, contact the admissions department of the French institution you wish to study at.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Temporary long-stay visa</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The&nbsp;<em>visa de long s&eacute;jour temporaire pour &eacute;tudes&nbsp;</em>is a temporary student visa that allows you to study in France for a period of up to six months. With this student visa for France you do&nbsp;<em>not</em>&nbsp;need to apply separately for a residence permit.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Long-stay visa</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Known as the&nbsp;<em>visa de long s&eacute;jour pour &eacute;tudes</em>&nbsp;or the extended-stay VLT-TS, the long-stay visa is what you need if you wish to study in France for longer than six months. This visa acts as a residence permit and lasts for the duration of your study period (normally three years for a bachelor&rsquo;s degree, two years for a master&rsquo;s program and four years for a PhD). Algerian nationals do not require the VLS-TS, but are subject to different provisions. Contact your institution or the French consulate/embassy in your own country for more information.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>How to apply for a student visa for France</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.topuniversities.com/sites/default/files/Student%20visa%20application%20form_0.jpg\" style=\"height:202px; width:300px\" title=\"\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Nationals from a number of countries will apply for their French student visa through Campus France, the country&rsquo;s official national agency for higher education and international students. Those students would also have been required to use Campus France to apply to their chosen French institutions, via the CEF procedure. See&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.campusfrance.org/en/page/a-country-using-cef-procedure\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">this list of countries</a>&nbsp;to find out if you need to apply for both your visa and your admission in this way.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If your country of origin is&nbsp;<em>not</em>&nbsp;listed in the link above, then you will be responsible for both your university application and your student visa application. Only once you have received acceptance onto a program at a French institution will you be eligible to apply for your student visa for France.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In order to apply for your visa, you will need to contact the French consulate in your home country and provide them with the following, when requested:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>An official acceptance letter onto an accredited program at a French institution. This should be on officially headed paper, featuring your full details, the details of your program of study and the start and end dates of study.</li>\r\n	<li>Proof of sufficient funds for living in the country. The current amount required is &euro;615 (US$820) per month, which can be shown with a bank statement, a guarantor&rsquo;s letter or a notice of funding from a loan, scholarship or grant.</li>\r\n	<li>Proof of return ticket home. Often this is in the form of the actual ticket or reservation showing the date of departure, but can be a handwritten statement of intent, including intended departure dates.</li>\r\n	<li>Proof of medical insurance (minimum cover &euro;30,000, US$40,150)</li>\r\n	<li>Proof of accommodation. Can be shown in the form of student housing confirmation or a certificate of board and lodging or &lsquo;<em>attestation d&rsquo;accueil&rsquo;</em>&nbsp;(if you&rsquo;re living with friends or relatives).</li>\r\n	<li>Proof of proficiency in French, if you are studying a French-language course.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>On arrival in France</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.topuniversities.com/sites/default/files/french_flag.jpg\" style=\"width:300px\" title=\"\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>When you arrive in France with an extended stay VLS-TS, you will need to send the official form which was presented to you along with your visa to the French Office of Immigration and Integration (OFII). This can be by registered mail, or in person if you reside in Paris. In the same letter, you should also provide a copy of your valid passport, including pages showing your identity and the stamp issued upon entry into France.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Once your form and copied passport pages have been received, you will be sent a receipt of confirmation with further instructions on your next steps if required. This may be an instruction to obtain a medical examination if you have not previously received one in your country of origin.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Often your institution of study will help you with this part of the process. In some cases, an agreement exists between the OFII and the school in question, meaning documents can be submitted to the school instead of the French authorities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In all instances, you will be expected to pay a tax of &euro;58 (US$78) to handle administration costs.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Working in France with a French student visa</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.topuniversities.com/sites/default/files/Euro_1.jpg\" style=\"height:144px; width:152px\" title=\"\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>With a valid residence permit (the VLS-TS functions as such), as an international student you are eligible to take on paid work for 964 hours annually (this equates to about 60% full-time employment). This number of hours is configured for work between the periods of 1 September to 31 August. Eligible work hours between September and June are (up to) 670, while July to August is (up to) 300 hours.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px\">for more information :&nbsp;https://www.topuniversities.com/student-info/studying-abroad/how-get-student-visa-france</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-18', 1),
(77, 'French Guiana', 'GUF', 'gf.png', '<p><span style=\"font-size:20px\">&nbsp;for more information&nbsp; : https://www.visahq.de/en/french-guiana/</span></p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-18', 1),
(78, 'French Polynesia', 'PYF', 'pf.png', '<p><span style=\"font-size:20px\">for all information plz click heare :&nbsp;https://tahititourisme.com/en-us/travel-planner/tahiti-visa-requirements/</span></p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-18', 1),
(79, 'French Southern Territories', 'ATF', 'tf.png', '<h1>France Visa Application Requirements, Fees and Guidelines</h1>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"France Visa Application Requirements, Fees and Guidelines\" src=\"https://www.schengenvisainfo.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/France-Schengen-Visa-300x300.jpg\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Depending on the purpose of your travel to France, there are different types of visas that will apply to the occasion.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Whether you are planning to go on a visit, study or work and reside in France permanently, you will have to apply for a different France Schengen Visa, accordingly.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nYou can apply for the France Visa since 1997 when France, as a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.schengenvisainfo.com/eu-countries/\">Member of the European Union</a><strong><u>,</u></strong>&nbsp;also became a member state of the Schengen Area.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Monaco &ndash; a European microstate/city-state located within France &ndash; is considered part of the Schengen Area although it did not officially sign the particular documents of the agreement. Besides, no border control is performed for the Schengen countries surrounding it!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On the other hand, Andorra as another microstate located between France and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.schengenvisainfo.com/spain-visa/\">Spain</a>&nbsp;performs border controls, therefore to enter it you should obtain a multi-entry Schengen visa since you should enter the Schengen Area while going or leaving Andorra.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>France Entry Restrictions in Response to Coronavirus</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Due to the Coronavirus outbreak, France, as well as the rest of the EU and Schengen Area members imposed an EU-wide entry ban on third-country nationals in mid-March 2020.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Travellers from Australia, Japan, New Zealand, Rwanda, Singapore, South Korea, Thailand can enter without restrictions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><ins><ins><ins><iframe frameborder=\"0\" height=\"280\" id=\"aswift_2\" name=\"aswift_2\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"https://googleads.g.doubleclick.net/pagead/ads?guci=2.2.0.0.2.2.0.0&amp;client=ca-pub-9770803606730350&amp;output=html&amp;h=280&amp;adk=393542921&amp;adf=782271616&amp;pi=t.aa~a.894851566~i.9~rp.4&amp;w=660&amp;fwrn=4&amp;fwrnh=100&amp;lmt=1613623850&amp;num_ads=1&amp;rafmt=1&amp;armr=3&amp;sem=mc&amp;pwprc=8902246954&amp;psa=0&amp;ad_type=text_image&amp;format=660x280&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.schengenvisainfo.com%2Ffrance-visa%2F&amp;flash=0&amp;fwr=0&amp;pra=3&amp;rh=165&amp;rw=660&amp;rpe=1&amp;resp_fmts=3&amp;wgl=1&amp;fa=27&amp;adsid=ChEIgJqzgQYQqZ2SzOmfnf6lARI5AKapXTroBHJ3lkmW2T1CS9oez8n74WrwCknWpyQ6XepzIpIs7Hm3uwkMEjC7YEJ6CNu8kpPX3N7X&amp;dt=1613623850749&amp;bpp=4&amp;bdt=3085&amp;idt=-M&amp;shv=r20210211&amp;cbv=r20190131&amp;ptt=9&amp;saldr=aa&amp;abxe=1&amp;cookie=ID%3Dc3164079019d667c-221ab08a10c6007c%3AT%3D1613623851%3ART%3D1613623851%3AS%3DALNI_MZzc08WipuxMzTfWQB6j-IaXuaHJw&amp;prev_fmts=0x0%2C660x280&amp;nras=2&amp;correlator=416507051565&amp;frm=20&amp;pv=1&amp;ga_vid=1902242764.1613623850&amp;ga_sid=1613623850&amp;ga_hid=1412349246&amp;ga_fc=0&amp;u_tz=360&amp;u_his=24&amp;u_java=0&amp;u_h=768&amp;u_w=1366&amp;u_ah=728&amp;u_aw=1366&amp;u_cd=24&amp;u_nplug=3&amp;u_nmime=4&amp;adx=475&amp;ady=782&amp;biw=1349&amp;bih=625&amp;scr_x=0&amp;scr_y=0&amp;eid=21066923%2C21068084%2C21068769%2C21068893&amp;oid=3&amp;pvsid=3840282482702477&amp;pem=561&amp;ref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2F&amp;rx=0&amp;eae=0&amp;fc=1408&amp;brdim=0%2C0%2C0%2C0%2C1366%2C0%2C1366%2C728%2C1366%2C625&amp;vis=1&amp;rsz=%7C%7Cs%7C&amp;abl=NS&amp;fu=8320&amp;bc=31&amp;ifi=3&amp;uci=a!3&amp;btvi=2&amp;fsb=1&amp;xpc=2TS7nvabdb&amp;p=https%3A//www.schengenvisainfo.com&amp;dtd=70\" width=\"660\"></iframe></ins></ins></ins></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Residents of these countries must have a certificate corresponding to their situation:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>for an international trip, Authorized by derogation, from abroad to metropolitan France,</li>\r\n	<li>for an international trip from abroad to an overseas community.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>In addition, third-country residents who meet at least one of the statements listed below can also enter France:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Travellers in transit for less than 24h in an international zone to reach their country of origin and who have a ticket for that country</li>\r\n	<li>Personnel of diplomatic and consular missions, as well as international organizations headquartered or having an office in France, and their partners and children.</li>\r\n	<li>Foreign health professionals helping to fight COVID-19</li>\r\n	<li>Foreign crews and personnel operating passenger and cargo flights or travelling as passengers to reach their departure base</li>\r\n	<li>Foreign nationals carrying out international goods transport</li>\r\n	<li>Foreign navy personnel carrying out international goods transport or working on fishing boats</li>\r\n	<li>A fortnight of quarantine upon arrival in France is mandatory for third-country residents.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Who does and who don&rsquo;t need a&nbsp;Visa to enter France?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Not to every foreigner and not for every territory of France applies the same visa policy. As such, visa exemptions are greatly influenced by dissimilar factors, where the major ones are: foreigner&rsquo;s nationality, the territory of the France that the applicant seeks to visit, foreigner&rsquo;s residence status in Schengen Area or specifically in France, the purpose of visit, as well as duration of stay.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px\">for more informatiomn :&nbsp;https://www.schengenvisainfo.com/france-visa/</span></p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-18', 1),
(80, 'Gabon', 'GAB', 'ga.png', '<h1>Gabon - Apply for a Student Visa</h1>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wikiprocedure.com/index.php/Special:ThisForm?catname=Gabon\">Create Procedure for Gabon</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img src=\"https://trk.justanswer.com/aff_i?offer_id=2&amp;aff_id=10349&amp;url_id=34&amp;file_id=1610\" style=\"height:0px; width:0px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Contents</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.wikiprocedure.com/index.php/Gabon_-_Apply_for_a_Student_Visa#Procedure\">1Procedure</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.wikiprocedure.com/index.php/Gabon_-_Apply_for_a_Student_Visa#Required_Documents\">2Required Documents</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.wikiprocedure.com/index.php/Gabon_-_Apply_for_a_Student_Visa#Office_Locations_.26_Contacts\">3Office Locations &amp; Contacts</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.wikiprocedure.com/index.php/Gabon_-_Apply_for_a_Student_Visa#Eligibility\">4Eligibility</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.wikiprocedure.com/index.php/Gabon_-_Apply_for_a_Student_Visa#Fees\">5Fees</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.wikiprocedure.com/index.php/Gabon_-_Apply_for_a_Student_Visa#Validity\">6Validity</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.wikiprocedure.com/index.php/Gabon_-_Apply_for_a_Student_Visa#Documents_to_Use\">7Documents to Use</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.wikiprocedure.com/index.php/Gabon_-_Apply_for_a_Student_Visa#Sample_Documents\">8Sample Documents</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.wikiprocedure.com/index.php/Gabon_-_Apply_for_a_Student_Visa#Processing_Time\">9Processing Time</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.wikiprocedure.com/index.php/Gabon_-_Apply_for_a_Student_Visa#Related_Videos\">10Related Videos</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.wikiprocedure.com/index.php/Gabon_-_Apply_for_a_Student_Visa#Instructions\">11Instructions</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.wikiprocedure.com/index.php/Gabon_-_Apply_for_a_Student_Visa#Required_Information\">12Required Information</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.wikiprocedure.com/index.php/Gabon_-_Apply_for_a_Student_Visa#Need_for_the_Document\">13Need for the Document</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.wikiprocedure.com/index.php/Gabon_-_Apply_for_a_Student_Visa#Information_which_might_help\">14Information which might help</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.wikiprocedure.com/index.php/Gabon_-_Apply_for_a_Student_Visa#Other_uses_of_the_Document.2FCertificate\">15Other uses of the Document/Certificate</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://www.wikiprocedure.com/index.php/Gabon_-_Apply_for_a_Student_Visa#External_Links\">16External Links</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Procedure[<a href=\"https://www.wikiprocedure.com/index.php?title=Gabon_-_Apply_for_a_Student_Visa&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Procedure\">edit</a>]</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Enter to Gabon with a Student visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Register your name at the nearest neighborhood police station within the first seven days of your arrival in Gabon.</li>\r\n	<li>Depending on where your classes are held, take your passport and your complete address written on a piece of paper the immigration officer in Libreville. If you are American, Canadian, or an EU citizen, you are not to register upon arrival to Gabon.</li>\r\n	<li>Without an appropriate visa from the Gabon government, you will be subject to deportation.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Within 30 days of arrival in Gabon, you must complete the application process to obtain a student residence visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Note</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The student residence visa is renewed on a yearly basis</li>\r\n	<li>Non-Gabon full-time students are entitled to University certification to obtain a student residence visa.</li>\r\n	<li>Full time status for Undergraduate, Non-degree Undergraduate is 12 credit hours. As for Graduate, Non-degree Graduate is 9 credit hours.</li>\r\n	<li>If your parents are permanent residents of Gabon, you are not required to obtain a student residence visa provided that you are still a dependent of your parent.</li>\r\n	<li>If you are an Gabonese/dual national male student or your father is Gabonese, the Gabon government recognizes you as a citizen of Gabon.</li>\r\n	<li>You are entitled to a six-month stay in Gabon as an Gabonese citizen without any obligations.</li>\r\n	<li>The student can stay 60 days after completion of their academic program. The student is expected to complete their studies in the nominated time.</li>\r\n	<li>A Study visa allows the holders to live and work (in a restricted manner) in Gabon for as long as they need to complete their course in order to help support themselves and any dependents.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The Student visa form from your college or university is necessary to support your application for the visa. Remember that each International student visa is different and what visa you need to apply for depends on your special circumstances in Gabon.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The most important thing to do before you apply for your international student visa is funding for your studies in Gabon.</li>\r\n	<li>You need funding for your education and your living expenses while you are in Gabon</li>\r\n	<li>Remember that you cannot work while in Gabon on a student visa.</li>\r\n	<li>The financials for your student stay in Gabon has to be in place to have a chance at getting a student visa, don&#39;t rely on potential income</li>\r\n	<li>The income you show on your application must be equal to or exceed the costs of the first year of studies.</li>\r\n	<li>It&#39;s important that you contact your university or college of your choice, and they will inform you what they need from you in order to determine that you are academically eligible to study at their college or university.</li>\r\n	<li>Among other requirements you need to show your school that you have enough money to support yourself while studying at their school. You also need to have health insurance in Gabon as the cost of health care without insurance can be a hefty bill.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The following things you will need at the Gabon Embassy.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>You will have to pay a non-refundable application fee.</li>\r\n	<li>If your visa does not get approved you will not get your money back so check your documents well before applying.</li>\r\n	<li>Private medical insurance must be arranged and documentary evidence of this must be provided.</li>\r\n	<li>Application form need to be completed and sign, this form you will get at the Gabon Embassy.</li>\r\n	<li>You need a valid passport with passport expiration date of 6 month beyond your intended study in Gabon.</li>\r\n	<li>You need a photograph 1 by inches square (37 x 37mm) showing your full face</li>\r\n	<li>If you are applying for a F1 student visa remember you I-20A-B form from your college or university.</li>\r\n	<li>If you are applying for a student visa bring the proof that you have enough money to support yourself to the Gabon Embassy. It must be shown that the course fees have been paid in full.</li>\r\n	<li>It is very important when speaking to the Gabon Embassy officer; make sure that you prove to them that you have strong family ties in your home country and that you will leave Gabon after completion of your education there.</li>\r\n	<li>This is very important in your application process. Proof of ties to your home country could be family there mother,father brother sister. Letter from a future employer or a car in your name that you still have in your home country. Anything that you can show that you are coming back is good when you talk to the Gabon officer at the embassy.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>required Documents[<a href=\"https://www.wikiprocedure.com/index.php?title=Gabon_-_Apply_for_a_Student_Visa&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Required Documents\">edit</a>]</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Valid passport</li>\r\n	<li>A visa cover letter;</li>\r\n	<li>Covering letter from School / Tertiary Institutions / University addressed to Commissioner Immigration Control Department</li>\r\n	<li>admission letter from School / Tertiary Institutions / University;</li>\r\n	<li>Copies of parents passports</li>\r\n	<li>Covering letter from school to immigration department indicating year of admission and duration of study;</li>\r\n	<li>Attach copies of parents Immigration status like work permit if parents are residents in Gabon and</li>\r\n	<li>Parents do not live or work in Egypt, applicants should attach Letter from parent acknowledging relationship of the resident guardian and child or student in Gabon, consent or covering letter from guardian addressed to the Commissioner Immigration Control Department.,</li>\r\n	<li>Immigration status of host or guardian e.g. work permit or Passport.</li>\r\n	<li>Attach identification card issued by institution of learning.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Students undertaking post graduate program should provide copies of previous academic qualifications.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Payment slips</li>\r\n	<li>Residential Permit</li>\r\n	<li>A recent colored passport size photo with white background</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px\">for more information :&nbsp;https://www.wikiprocedure.com/index.php/Gabon_-_Apply_for_a_Student_Visa</span></p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-18', 1);
