(96, 'Haiti', 'HTI', 'ht.png', '<h4>&nbsp;Basic information</h4>\r\n\r\n<h5>for Haiti</h5>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.0.0/svg/2714.svg\" />&nbsp;Visa Consultancy</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bangladeshi Nationals can get 90 day visa issued on arrival for US$50.&nbsp; And need just a passport valid for six months and a return ticket. Your entry stamp entitles you to stay for up to 90 days. You&rsquo;ll also be given a green entry card to be produced on departure from Haiti &ndash; keep it carefully during your visit don&rsquo;t lose the</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:22px\">for more information :&nbsp;https://visathing.com/country/haiti/</span></p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-18', 1),
(97, 'Heard Island and McDonald Isla', 'HMD', 'hm.png', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>Studying in Ireland</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>There are eight universities in Ireland, all providing a wide variety of undergraduate or postgraduate courses to the 35,000 international students from 160 countries who currently study there. Located on the western coast of Europe, Ireland is a member of the European Union and, following Brexit, will soon be the&nbsp;only English speaking country in the Eurozone. Irish universities offer a fantastic higher education experience in a uniquely beautiful setting.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Irish qualifications are the same as the UK equivalents, so your&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.studyin-uk.com.bd/study-options/undergraduate/\">undergraduate</a>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.studyin-uk.com.bd/study-options/postgraduate-and-masters-degree/\">postgraduate</a>&nbsp;degree carries just as much value when you begin your career. The&nbsp;Free Fees Initiative&nbsp;for&nbsp;EU students (see below) enables those who meet the criteria to avoid paying tuition fees.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dublin, the Irish capital, has been voted by Lonely Planet as the world&rsquo;s friendliest city on multiple occasion and many of the largest companies in the world such as&nbsp;Google, Medtronics and Microsoft have offices there.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Tuition fees in Ireland</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>- Free Fees&nbsp;Initiative</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The Free Fees&nbsp;Initiative in Ireland will see your tuition fees paid to the university by Ireland&rsquo;s Higher Education Authority. To qualify for the Free Fees&nbsp;scheme you must meet the following criteria:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>You have lived in the EU for at least three of the previous five years</li>\r\n	<li>You are enrolling on your first undergraduate course</li>\r\n	<li>Your course lasts at least two-years and is full-time</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>More information can be found on the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.studentfinance.ie/mp9377/course-fees/index.html\">Student Finance Ireland</a>&nbsp;website.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Student visa requirements in Ireland</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Bangladeshi students must apply for a&nbsp;visa to enter Ireland before they travel. Students will be required to have accepted an offer of a recognised programme of study in Ireland and to have a receipt of payment letter from their institution before they can begin the process of applying for their overseas visa to study in Ireland.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Study at an Irish university</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are interested in studying at an Irish university,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.studyin-uk.com.bd/consultation/\">arrange your free consultation</a>&nbsp;in Dhaka today.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Ireland University Rankings</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:22px\">for more information :&nbsp;http://www.studyin-uk.com.bd/uk-study-info/study-in-ireland/</span></p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-18', 1),
(98, 'Honduras', 'HND', 'hn.png', '<h4>&nbsp;Basic information</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bangladeshi nations need visa to enter in Honduras. But there is no Embassy or Consulate office in Dhaka, Bangladesh. However, there is no Honduras Embassy or consular office in New Delhi, India also. Therefore, if the applicant has a valid USA or Canada visa, then S/he can get an on arrival visa. If the applicant does not have any valid USA or Canada visa, then the inviting party in Honduras needs to arrange an Immigration Approval from Honduras Ministry of Home Affairs and send it to the applicant; with the approval, S/he can get an on arrival visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Website:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.hondurasemb.org/site/\">http://www.hondurasemb.org/site/</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>&nbsp;Check List</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Require documents:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Passport valid for 6 months from date of arrival required by all.</li>\r\n	<li>Two passport-size photos.</li>\r\n	<li>Completed application form.</li>\r\n	<li>travel schedule and proof of residence</li>\r\n	<li>Return Air Ticket</li>\r\n	<li>Letter affirming leave of absence from Employer, or letter from University plus form I-20 confirming continued enrollment.</li>\r\n	<li>Copy of recent bank statement &ndash; additional financial information may be required.</li>\r\n	<li>For business visas, company letters giving full details and confirming financial responsibility for the applicant</li>\r\n	<li>A yellow fever vaccination certificate is required from all travelers arriving within 6 days from infected areas.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:22px\">for more information :&nbsp;https://visathing.com/country/honduras/</span></p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-18', 1),
(99, 'Hong Kong', 'HKG', 'hk.png', '<h1>Hong Kong (SAR China) Visa from Bangladesh<br />\r\n<a href=\"https://visathing.com/continent/asia/\" rel=\"tag\">Asia</a></h1>\r\n\r\n<p>Capital City:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Hong Kong</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Currency:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Hong Kong Dollar (HKD)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Local Time:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>GMT + 8</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Telephone Code:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>+ 852</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bank:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Closed on Saturday afternoon and Sunday.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Exchange Rate:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1.00 HKD (Hong Kong Dollar) is equivalent to 10.10 BDT</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>&nbsp;Basic information</h4>\r\n\r\n<h5>For Hong Kong, VISAThing provides</h5>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.0.0/svg/2714.svg\" />&nbsp;Visa Consultancy</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Chinese Embassy is only mandated to issue limited kinds of visas for Hong Kong.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You have to apply at the Immigration Office in Hong Kong to get the visa. An applicant may choose any of the below two processes:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Process 1:&nbsp;</strong>An applicant can submit passport copy and all the necessary documents listed below at Dragon Airlines and pay the necessary fees. They will submit your application at Hong Kong Immigration Department for visa approval. Once the visa is approved, then the immigration will send a visa sticker to the&nbsp;applicant. Through that visa, an applicant can fly to Hong Kong.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Process 2:&nbsp;</strong>An applicant get the immigration approval through the Host Company or Tour Operators in Hong Kong. They need to apply on behalf of applicant at the Immigration Department with the fee. The processing time is at least 35 days in both processes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>&nbsp;Visa Consultancy Fee</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>** 15% VAT is applicable on VISAThing Express&rsquo; service (consultancy) charge.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5>&nbsp;Consultancy Fee</h5>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Service</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Fee (BDT)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Consultancy</p>\r\n\r\n<p>10,000/-</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>&nbsp;Check List</h2>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><strong>Tourist / Business Visa Requirements:</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Passport:</strong>latest passport copies(all pages)including visas and endorsements<strong>&nbsp;</strong>(Original Passport must be shown at the time of submitting visa application)</li>\r\n	<li>Copy of previous passports and visas issued.<br />\r\n	<strong>Hong Kong (SAR China)&nbsp;Visa Application Form:</strong>Application form &ndash; ID1003A &amp; ID1003B must be signed by the applicant. Visa form is also available at this web site link:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.immd.gov.hk/pdforms/ID1003A.pdf\">Click Here</a>&nbsp;Form &ndash; ID1003B must be filled by the sponsor with sign &amp; seal and copy of Hong Kong identity card or filled by applicants with the information of the invitation letter from Hong Kong. Form &ndash; ID520 (Applicant&rsquo;s Family Background) must be filled and signed by the applicant. Authorization letter (Must be filled and signed by the applicant).</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Photo Specification:</strong>Two recent passport size photographs with 60-80% face coverage, white background and without border&nbsp;(Size: 35mm x 45mm)</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Covering-Letter:</strong>Covering Letter from applicant&nbsp;name, designation, Passport Number, purpose and outlining who will be responsible for the full costs of the trip &ndash; travel, accommodation, expenses etc.&nbsp;Addressed to &ndash; The Visa Officer, Embassy of Hong Kong (SAR China), Dhaka.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Invitation Letter:&nbsp;</strong>Invitation letter from company in Hong Kong mentioning purpose of visit, length of stay, number of visits required and taking the responsibility of repatriation of the applicant</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Forwarding-Letter:</strong><br />\r\n	<strong>a)&nbsp;</strong>Forwarding Letter / NOC from the applicant&rsquo;s company authority on the company&rsquo;s letter head stating applicant&rsquo;s name, designation, passport number, purpose and duration of visit.<br />\r\n	<strong>b)&nbsp;</strong>Visa request letter&nbsp;from the educational institute or student card/evidence of school enrollment (if student)</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Proof of Occupation:</strong><br />\r\n	<strong>a)&nbsp;</strong>Company registration certificate&nbsp;(original notarized English translated and photocopy of the original)<br />\r\n	<strong>b)&nbsp;</strong>Office ID card copy&nbsp;&amp; Visiting cards.<br />\r\n	<strong>c)&nbsp;</strong>Income Tax Certificate(Tin) copy.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Financials:</strong><br />\r\n	<strong>a)</strong>&nbsp;Company&rsquo;s or Personal Bank Statement for last six months mentioning the Bank&rsquo;s name, Bank&rsquo;s Telephone Number clearly.<br />\r\n	<strong>b)</strong>&nbsp;Salary slip for the last six months. (If Any)<br />\r\n	<strong>c)</strong>&nbsp;Marriage certificate in English with notary. (If traveling with spouse)</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Ticket &amp; Hotel Reservation:&nbsp;</strong>Ticket Itinerary and Hotel Booking (If one can manage invitation letter &amp; if it&rsquo;s written in that invitation letter that&nbsp;he/she can live invitation sender&rsquo;s house or all expenses will be beard by person. Then no need of Hotel booking)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Note:</strong>&nbsp;One set photocopies of all original documents.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:24px\">for more information :&nbsp;https://visathing.com/country/hong-kong-sar-china/&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-18', 1),
(100, 'Hungary', 'HUN', 'hu.png', '<h2>Hungary</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.educations.com/search/hungary\">Find a Program in Hungary</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Visa Requirements for Education in Hungary</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>International students who want to stay in Hungary for more than 90 consecutive days and who are not EU citizens are required to apply for a long-term student visa to stay in the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Student visas requirements for Hungary vary, therefore it&#39;s important to enquire well in advance about the entry regulations which apply to your home country. To receive a student visa for Hungary, you must first have an offer from a Hungarian university. You can only apply for your student visa prior to your departure from the Hungarian Consulate or Embassy that has jurisdiction in your state or country of permanent residence. Processing a visa usually takes around one month, but could be longer so make sure you apply as early as possible to avoid any unnecessary complications.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDocuments required for your student visa&nbsp;for Hungary are:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Proof of having paid the tuition fee</li>\r\n	<li>An acceptance letter from the university regarding your admission</li>\r\n	<li>Passport valid at least 6 months beyond your date of entry</li>\r\n	<li>Copy of the photograph page of your passport</li>\r\n	<li>Passport photo no more than 6 months old</li>\r\n	<li>Proof of health insurance</li>\r\n	<li>Proof of address or housing in Hungary</li>\r\n	<li>Proof of sufficient funds to cover living expenses in the form of bank assurance/statement</li>\r\n	<li>Visa application form</li>\r\n	<li>3 stamped envelopes addressed to the applicant</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>When the consulates requires an appointment, you may need to scheduled it around 4 to 6 weeks in advance because appointment times are limited. After the appointment, the visa processing time usually&nbsp;takes an additional 1 to 4 weeks.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You will need to apply for your residence permit within 15 days of arrival in Hungary. This applies to both EU and non-EU citizens planning to stay in Hungary for longer than 90 days.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To apply for a residence permit, EU and EEA citizens need to submit the following documents:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Proof of payment of tuition fees</li>\r\n	<li>Approval document of the host university in Hungary</li>\r\n	<li>Proof of health insurance</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:24px\">for more information :&nbsp;https://www.educations.com/study-guides/europe/study-in-hungary/student-visa-7855</span></p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-18', 1),
