(122, 'Latvia', 'LVA', 'lv.png', '<p><strong>Study in Latvia from Bangladesh:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Those pursuing study abroad in Latvia will also notice that the nation&rsquo;s openness to outside influences is evident in its education system, as Latvian higher education institutions are active members of international organizations in various fields of study.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nAccording to the Territorial Competence, Bangladeshi nationals are subjected to apply for a Long Stay visa with the Embassy of Latvia in India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Embassy of Latvia, India<br />\r\nAddress:<br />\r\nB8 Anand Niketan, 110021 New Delhi<br />\r\nPhone: +91 11 49859100<br />\r\nEmbassy&#39;s e-mail: embassy.india@mfa.gov.lv<br />\r\nConsular e-mail: consulate.india@mfa.gov.lv</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Basic Requirements for Latvian Residence Permit and Long-stay Visa:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bangladeshi students, who intend to enter Latvia on study purposes, must apply for a residence permit at the Embassy of Latvia in India in person. Once the decision on granting rights of residence is made, student can apply for a long stay visa at the Embassy of Latvia in India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Documents to be submitted in order to receive a residence permit:<br />\r\n A definite sample form for a residence permit request;<br />\r\n A photograph;<br />\r\n A statement on punishability issued by a competent institution of the citizenship or the host country (for a foreigner more than 14-year-old), if a foreigner has resided in that country longer than 12 months.<br />\r\n A document confirming the necessary subsistence;<br />\r\n A document confirming the envisaged place of residence in the Republic of Latvia and the rights to stay there;<br />\r\n A document confirming the state duty payment;<br />\r\n An agreement on studies in the Republic of Latvia;<br />\r\n Documents confirming that you have acquired the necessary education to start the studies;<br />\r\n[Before the submission of the documents your inviter shall approve the call at the Office of Citizenship and Migration Affairs.]</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Documents required for a visa application:<br />\r\n A valid travel document (passport)<br />\r\n A visa application form filled out and signed;<br />\r\n A photograph;<br />\r\n A copy of a document confirming that the applicant has adequate and valid travel medical insurance policy;<br />\r\n Documents, including the purpose of the journey and documents in relation to accommodation, or documents indicating that a letter of invitation has been approved by the OCMA (the invitation is valid for 6 months from the date of approval);<br />\r\n Documents indicating that the applicant possesses sufficient means of subsistence both for the duration of the intended stay and for the return to his country of origin or residence, or for the transit to a third country into which he is certain to be admitted (14 EUR per day);<br />\r\n A receipt confirming the fee payment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Fee:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; Student Visa Fee (Singly/Double Entry)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; Euro 60/ INR 4600/ BDT 6000<br />\r\n&nbsp; Student Visa Fee ( Multiple Entry)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Euro 85.37/ INR 6400/ BDT 8650<br />\r\n&nbsp; Indian VFS Service Charge&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; INR 1573/ BDT 2000</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Processing time:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Approximate processing time is 80 to 90 working days (Time may vary depending on the university and embassy)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Please call 01958-666999 &amp; 01958-666900 for more information.</p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2018-12-23', 1),
(123, 'Lebanon', 'LBN', 'lb.png', '<p><span style=\"font-size:20px\">al for information please click:&nbsp; heare&nbsp;https://stickervisa.com/lebanon/#:~:text=Original%20Passport%20of%20the%20applicant,and%20signed%20by%20the%20applicant.</span></p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-20', 1),
(124, 'Lesotho', 'LSO', 'ls.png', '<h1>Lesotho<br />\r\n<a href=\"https://visathing.com/continent/africa/\" rel=\"tag\">Africa</a></h1>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bangladeshi Nationals do not require a visa to enter Lesotho for travelling up to 90 days. Before travelling you must need to carry following documents.</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Valid passport</li>\r\n	<li>One passport-size photograph</li>\r\n	<li>Copy of the return ticket or itinerary.</li>\r\n	<li>Police Clearance from country of origin.</li>\r\n	<li>Invitation letter from the inviting party (if any)</li>\r\n	<li>A vaccination certificate is required from visitors coming from countries where cholera or yellow fever is endemic.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>** VISAThing!<sub>TM</sub>&nbsp;provides&nbsp;<strong>personalized visa consultancy service</strong>&nbsp;for Lesotho (Consultancy fee applicable).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:24px\">fore more information :&nbsp; https://visathing.com/country/lesotho/</span></p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-20', 1),
(125, 'Liberia', 'LBR', 'lr.png', '<h4>&nbsp;Basic information</h4>\r\n\r\n<h5>For&nbsp;Liberia, VISAThing provides</h5>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>&nbsp;Visa Consultancy</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As there is no Embassy or Consulate of Liberian in Dhaka, Bangladesh. Visitors to Liberia can apply in the nearest Liberian Embassy. In Asia, Embassies are in Tokyo, Japan and Beijing, China.&nbsp;Visitors can apply through their contacts in Liberia for an Airport Visa They can apply to the Immigration Dept. in Liberia with a copy to Ministry of Foreign Affairs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>EMBASSY OF THE REPUBLIC OF LIBERIA</strong><br />\r\nShirokane K House 4-14-12 Shirokane, Minato-ku<br />\r\nTokyo-1080072, Japan</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Telephone:</strong>&nbsp;03-3441-7720<br />\r\n(from overseas +81-3-3441-7720)<br />\r\n<strong>Fax:</strong>&nbsp;03-3441-7728<br />\r\n(from overseas +81-3-3441-7728)<br />\r\n<strong>Email:</strong>&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:embassyofliberia@heart.ocn.ne.jp\">embassyofliberia@heart.ocn.ne.jp</a><br />\r\n<strong>Website:</strong>&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.liberianembassyjp.org/\">www.liberianembassyjp.org</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>&nbsp;Check List</h2>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>Requirements for VISA</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Fully completed visa form for Liberia and mandatory declaration</li>\r\n	<li>Two recent passport-size photos&nbsp;(WHITE BACK GROUND/RED (LONG SERVICE)</li>\r\n	<li>Valid national passport and one copy</li>\r\n	<li>Original of valid visa for anyone who is national of another country and one copy</li>\r\n	<li>Your latest bank account statement and one copy</li>\r\n	<li>Confirmation letter from your travel health insurance for Liberia stating the coverage and one copy</li>\r\n	<li>Reference letter from your employer or education establishment</li>\r\n	<li>Proof of group travel/ hotel room booking reservation in Liberia / air ticket reservation for Liberia and one copy</li>\r\n	<li>Vaccination against yellow fever</li>\r\n	<li>Evidence of financial support</li>\r\n	<li>Letter of invitation from Liberia with the name of a contact person and the telephone number including e-mail (if any)</li>\r\n	<li>1 letter from your company requesting for visa, if self-employed articles of incorporation of your company.</li>\r\n	<li>A fee of 8,000 JPY for three months (single entry), 16,000 JPY&nbsp;for three months (multiple entries). Payment will be done by applicant (s) into consular&rsquo;s account after which the proof of payment will be submitted to the embassy.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Please notice:</strong>&nbsp;In individual circumstances, you might be expected to produce additional paperwork. Liberian embassy guidelines and regulations can and do, change over night.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px\">for all information :&nbsp;https://visathing.com/country/liberia/</span></p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-20', 1),
