(143, 'Mexico', 'MEX', 'mx.png', '<h2>&nbsp;Check List</h2>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>Tourist Visa</strong>&nbsp;<strong>Requirements:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Application form duly filled.</li>\r\n	<li>Passport valid for at least six months.</li>\r\n	<li>A recent passport-sized photograph (4.5 CM X 3.5 CM), white background, no glasses and forehead.</li>\r\n	<li>Covering letter given by your organization and duly signed by the competent authority.</li>\r\n	<li>Copy of Personal Bank Statement (last 6 months).</li>\r\n	<li>Copy of Personal Income Tax Return (ITR) or Form 16 (last 3 years).</li>\r\n	<li>Flight tentative itinerary.</li>\r\n	<li>Visa fee.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>&nbsp;Business visa requirements:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Application form duly filled.</li>\r\n	<li>Passport valid for at least six months.</li>\r\n	<li>A recent passport-sized photograph (4.5 CM X 3.5 CM), white background, no glasses and forehead.</li>\r\n	<li>Covering letter given by your organization and duly signed by the competent authority.</li>\r\n	<li>Letter of Invitation given by Mexican counterpart and duly signed by the authorized person.</li>\r\n	<li>Copy of Personal Bank Statement (last 6 months).</li>\r\n	<li>Copy of Personal Income Tax Return (ITR) or Form 16 (last 3 years).</li>\r\n	<li>Flight tentative itinerary.</li>\r\n	<li>Visa fee.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>Note:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Personal presence of the applicant is mandatory for biometric process and interview.</li>\r\n	<li>Processing visa time is two working days if the applicants fulfill all the visa requirements.</li>\r\n	<li>Holders of diplomatic or official or service passports and laissez passer to enter Mexico in official missions or in private trips please contact the personal of the Consular Section.</li>\r\n	<li>Clergy and minister of religion, please contact the personal of the Consular Section.</li>\r\n	<li>Entry to Mexico is subject to the discretion of the Immigration Officer.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>IMPORTANT:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>It is not possible to present your documents via courier or third party.&nbsp;If you are granted a Mexican visa you will be able to travel to Mexico. It does not guarantee entry to the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At the point of entry, Mexican immigration authorities may ask you some questions to confirm the reasons you are travelling, the length of your stay in Mexico and how you are financing your trip. The following questions are few examples of what you may be asked:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>How will you leave the country?</li>\r\n	<li>If you are on a student visa, what program are you enrolled in? Which is the host institution?</li>\r\n	<li>If you are on a work visa, who or what company is hiring you? What activities will you be engaging in within the company?</li>\r\n	<li>How long will you be staying in Mexico?</li>\r\n	<li>How will you cover your expenses?</li>\r\n	<li>Do you have any acquaintances in the country?</li>\r\n	<li>Where are you staying?</li>\r\n	<li>Why are you travelling to Mexico? What activities will you be engaging in?</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>As in all countries, Mexican immigration authorities will verify the authenticity of all the documents you present and the truthfulness of the information you provide. They will also confirm that no outright restriction exists.&nbsp;<strong>The reasons for your trip must match your visa type.&nbsp;</strong>Everyone visiting or living in Mexico has rights which must be respected. Foreigners have the right to contact their embassy or consulate.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:22px\"><strong>For more information</strong>&nbsp;:&nbsp;https://visathing.com/country/mexico/</span></p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-20', 1),
(144, 'Micronesia', 'FSM', 'fm.png', '<h5>&nbsp;</h5>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Upon arrival, all non-citizens without a valid entry permit must present a completed &ldquo;FSM Immigration Arrival and Departure Record.&rdquo; This form is furnished by a carrier prior to arrival at the point of entry. Those wishing to visit the FSM for a period exceeding 30 days must also complete a entry permit. A permit is not required for a person visiting the FSM for 30 days or less.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>&nbsp;Check List</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>ENTRY PERMIT REQUIREMENTS:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>You are required to submit this application form with the appropriate requirement(s) of an entry permit that you are</p>\r\n\r\n<p>applying for:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Photocopy of passport, including date passport issued and passport expiration date.</li>\r\n	<li>One passport-size photograph. (Please sign your name on the back of the photo).</li>\r\n	<li>Police clearance. (Must be obtained from your country of citizenship or from your place of residency within the last six (6) months).</li>\r\n	<li>Medical Clearance/Certificate. (May be obtained in the FSM).</li>\r\n	<li>Notarized Affidavit of Support/Dependency (if applicable to your case).</li>\r\n	<li>Requirements of Immigration Change of Status, Public Law 7-23 (if applicable)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px\">For more information please <strong>:&nbsp;</strong><strong>https://visathing.com/country/micronesia-federated-states/</strong></span></p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-20', 1),
(145, 'Moldova', 'MDA', 'md.png', '<h2>Moldova eVisa for the citizens of Bangladesh</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>iVisa | Updated on Feb 02, 2021</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you&#39;re planning a trip to Moldova, one of the first things you should think about is the fact that you may be required to get a visa before departure. Many nationalities do. Thankfully, Moldova has an electronic visa system, so instead of paying a visit to the nearest Moldovan consulate to get your visa, you can&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.ivisa.com/apply-online/MD?nationality=BD&amp;selectedVisaCategory=166\">acquire a Moldova eVisa online</a>. iVisa ensures a short and smooth online application process so you can apply with ease. You should read the answers to some of the most frequently asked questions below if you want to learn more about the Moldova eVisa.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>WHAT ARE THE REQUIREMENTS FOR A MOLDOVA EVISA?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Before you proceed to the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.ivisa.com/apply-online/MD?nationality=BD&amp;selectedVisaCategory=166\">application page</a>, you should make sure that you have all of the requirements on hand. The list is not exactly long, and chances are that you already have some of the documents and information needed. Here is what you will need for a successful application process:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Invitation letter - the letter must be issued by the Migration and Asylum Office of Moldova or by a government authority in the investment projects of interest for the national economy. Not all nationalities need to have such a document, but citizens of Bangladesh do.</li>\r\n	<li>Valid passport - your passport must be valid for at least 3 months after your date of intended departure from Moldova and include at least one blank page available for stamping. You will also need to upload a scanned copy of the information page for the application.</li>\r\n	<li>Photo - you will need to provide a recent photograph that meets all the guidelines for a valid passport photo.</li>\r\n	<li>Return flight ticket - this is to show proof that you are not planning to stay for longer than your eVisa allows.</li>\r\n	<li>Proof of accommodation - such as a hotel booking confirmation.</li>\r\n	<li>Bank statement</li>\r\n	<li>Proof of travel medical insurance</li>\r\n	<li>E-mail address - the eVisa will arrive via e-mail in PDF format. You will need to print it out before your departure.</li>\r\n	<li>Means of payment - iVisa accepts credit or debit cards, as well as PayPal, Alipay, or WeChat.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>HOW LONG DOES IT TAKE FOR MY APPLICATION TO BE PROCESSED?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>That is up to you. Choosing iVisa as your visa service means that you can select the processing speed of your application. You can choose from the following three options so that you can make the best possible choice for you:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Standard - you must wait&nbsp;16 days&nbsp;for your application to be processed</li>\r\n	<li>Rush - your&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.ivisa.com/apply-online/MD?nationality=BD&amp;selectedVisaCategory=166\">Moldova eVisa</a>&nbsp;arrives within&nbsp;13 days</li>\r\n	<li>Super Rush - it takes only&nbsp;11 days&nbsp;for your travel document to be ready</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>HOW MUCH DOES IT COST TO APPLY FOR A MOLDOVA EVISA ONLINE?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The cost of your&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.ivisa.com/apply-online/MD?nationality=BD&amp;selectedVisaCategory=166\">Moldova eVisa</a>&nbsp;depends on the chosen processing speed of your application. The faster the processing, the more you are charged. The prices, including the service fees, are as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Standard -&nbsp;USD 90.00</li>\r\n	<li>Rush -&nbsp;USD 110.00</li>\r\n	<li>Super Rush -&nbsp;USD 140.00</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:24px\">for all information :&nbsp;https://www.ivisa.com/moldova-blog/moldova-evisa-for-the-citizens-of-bangladesh</span></p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-20', 1),
(146, 'Monaco', 'MCO', 'mc.png', '<h4>&nbsp;Basic information</h4>\r\n\r\n<h5>For &nbsp;Monaco, VISAThing provides</h5>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>&nbsp;Visa Consultancy</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bangladeshi&nbsp;nationals who are permitted to enter metropolitan France for a short visit, are allowed to enter Monaco without a visa. Bangladeshi&nbsp;nationals who hold a residence permit issued by a Schengen State are also authorized to enter and stay in Monaco. Holders of a valid Schengen visa covering France or a visa with limited territorial validity (LTV) for France are permitted to enter and stay in Monaco. Holders of a Schengen visa should be in a position to produce documents in support of the purpose and conditions of their visit to Monaco.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The procedure for applying for a short-stay visa for Monaco follows the same conditions and rules applicable to the Schengen visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Long-stay visa:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>All long-stay visas are subject to prior consultations with the Monegasque authorities. No reason is assigned for rejected visa applications. For this one should apply to the France Embassy in India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Why Do You Need</strong>&nbsp;<strong>VISAThing&rsquo;s Ground Support</strong>?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some countries having embassies located in India requires personal presence of the visa applicant at the Embassy/VFS for in person interview or biometric data collection. The applicant must visit the embassy in India to submit the visa application.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Most of the applicants face difficulty in</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>preparing an error visa application with all the necessary documents</li>\r\n	<li>the submission procedures at the embassy</li>\r\n	<li>navigating through the city and finding suitable lodging&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.visathing.com/ground-support/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">&hellip;Read more</a></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h2>&nbsp;Check List</h2>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>color photographs (full face, no dark glasses, no head covering, plain white background only)</li>\r\n	<li>Valid passport (the validity of the passport has to exceed the end of the proposed trip by at least three months)</li>\r\n	<li>Clear photocopy of your passport data page (identification page)</li>\r\n	<li>Travel Health Insurance (to cover medical expenses at minimum of 30,000&ndash;Euro)</li>\r\n	<li>All documents have to be accompanied with the original document and one photocopy</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>For Business Visa:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Original invitation letter from a company</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Proof of sufficient foreign funds (bank statements for the past three months)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Certificate of Incorporation of the company in Bangladesh and/or Memorandum and Articles of Association (if applicable)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Evidence of former and current transactions in Bangladesh and/or abroad (e.g. bills of lading, receipts, contracts)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Proof of personal living conditions marriage certificate, birth certificate of children (if applicable)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Covering letter/introduction letter from the company or organization in Bangladesh explaining necessity to travel even if the applicant is the owner of the company</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>For Tourist Visa:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Guarantor&rsquo;s form/Formal Obligation signed by the host/ess and duly legalized by the aliens authority in Switzerland or proof of sufficient foreign funds</li>\r\n	<li>Proof of personal living conditions: marriage certificate, birth certificate of children (if applicable)</li>\r\n	<li>Hotel booking (if applicable) &ndash; not mail-printout</li>\r\n	<li>Additional, if employed by a company here in Bangladesh.</li>\r\n	<li>Leave letter of employer (with physical address and telephone number) stating the duration of leave and the function/profession of the applicant in the company</li>\r\n	<li>Pay slips of the last three months</li>\r\n	<li>Statement of private bank account of the last three months</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>For Transit Visa:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Valid visas for all other countries of destination after leaving the Schengen territory.</li>\r\n	<li>Confirmed reservation of flight</li>\r\n	<li>For first time travelers: Complete business papers (see above)</li>\r\n	<li>For transit&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:22px\">for more information :&nbsp;https://visathing.com/country/monaco/#:~:text=Bangladeshi%20nationals%20who%20are%20permitted,enter%20and%20stay%20in%20Monaco.</span></p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-20', 1),
(147, 'Mongolia', 'MNG', 'mn.png', '<h2>Check List</h2>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong><u>Tourist Visa Requirements</u></strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>1. Passport:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Original Passport with validity of minimum six months after the intended date of departure and minimum two blank pages for visa stamp.&nbsp;Photocopy of the applicant&rsquo;s passport (first and last page). Attach all your old passports (if any)</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>2. Mongolia Visa Application Form:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Two visa application form back to back duly filled and signed.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>3. Photo Specification:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Two recent passport size photographs with matt or semi matt finish, 60% &ndash; 80% face coverage, light background and without border (Size: 35mm x 45mm).<strong>&nbsp;Also Provide two visiting card.</strong><br />\r\n<strong><u>Please note:</u></strong>&nbsp;Photograph should not be more than 3 months old, scanned/stapled and should not be used in any of the previous visas.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>4. A Covering letter</strong>:</h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Explaining in detail the purpose and duration of the visit. The letter should be addressed to the Visa Officer &ndash; Embassy of Mongolia, New Delhi.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>5. An Immigration Approval</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>An Immigration Approval from the Department in Mongolia. Please contact your Inviter / Inviting Frined or Tour Operator to arrange the approval.&nbsp;<strong>Without the approval, we cannot submit the application at the Embassy.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>6. Forwarding-Letter:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Forwarding Letter from applicant on company&rsquo;s letter head stating his name, designation, passport number, purpose and duration of visit, duly signed by authorized signatory and addressed to &ndash; The Visa Officer, Embassy of Mongolia, New Delhi.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>7. Ticket &amp; Hotel:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Confirmed Air Ticket and Hotel booking.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>8.&nbsp;</strong><strong>Invitation or Tour Confirmation:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Attach if any.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>9. Financial:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Foreign exchange endorsement or copy of credit card or Bank Statement for last 6 months.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong><u>Business Visa Requirements:</u></strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>1. Passport:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Original Passport with validity of minimum six months after the intended date of departure and minimum two blank pages for visa stamp.&nbsp;Photocopy of the applicant&rsquo;s passport (first and last page). Attach all your old passports (if any)</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>2. Mongolia Visa Application Form</strong>:</h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Two visa application form back to back duly filled and signed.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>3. Photo Specification:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Two recent passport size photographs with matt or semi matt finish, 60% &ndash; 80% face coverage, light background and without border (Size: 35mm x 45mm).<strong>&nbsp;Also Provide two visiting card.</strong><br />\r\n<strong><u>Please note:</u></strong>&nbsp;Photograph should not be more than 3 months old, scanned/stapled and should not be used in any of the previous visas.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>4. A Covering letter</strong>:</h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Explaining in detail the purpose and duration of the visit. The letter should be addressed to the Visa Officer &ndash; Embassy of Mongolia, New Delhi.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>5. An Immigration Approval</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>An Immigration Approval from the Department in Mongolia. Please contact your Inviter to arrange the approval.&nbsp;<strong>Without the approval, we cannot submit the application at the Embassy.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>6. Forwarding-Letter:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Forwarding Letter from applicant on company&rsquo;s letter head stating his name, designation, passport number, purpose and duration of visit, duly signed by authorized signatory and addressed to the Visa Officer, Embassy of Mongolia, New Delhi.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>7. Invitation letter:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>An Invitation letter from Mongolian Company through Ministry of Foreign Affairs, Mongolia should be directly faxed to the Embassy.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>8. Financial:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Foreign exchange endorsement or copy of credit card or Bank Statement for last 6 months.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>9. Ticket &amp; Hotel:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Confirmed Air Ticket and Hotel booking.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>Please Note:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Single/Double/Multiple entry visas are available for Business category that depends on the approval.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong><u>Visa Requirements for Official or Diplomatic Passport:</u></strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>1. Passport:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Original Passport with validity of minimum six months after the intended date of departure and minimum two blank pages for visa stamp. Photocopy of the applicant&rsquo;s passport (first and last page). Attach all your old passports (if any).</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>2. A Covering letter</strong>:</h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Explaining in detail the purpose and duration of the visit. The letter should be addressed to the Visa Officer &ndash; Embassy of Mongolia, New Delhi.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>3. Forwarding-Letter:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Forwarding Letter from applicant on company&rsquo;s letter head stating his name, designation, passport number, purpose and duration of visit, duly signed by authorized signatory and addressed to &ndash; The Visa Officer, Embassy of Mongolia, New Delhi.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>4. Invitation letter:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>An Invitation letter from Mongolian Company through Ministry of Foreign Affairs, Mongolia should be directly faxed to the Embassy.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>5. Ticket &amp; Hotel:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Confirmed Air Ticket and Hotel booking.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>6. Mongolia Visa Application Form</strong>:</h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Two visa application form back to back duly filled and signed.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>7. Photo Specification:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Two recent passport size photographs with matt or semi matt finish, 60% &ndash; 80% face coverage, light background and without border (Size: 35mm x 45mm). Also Provide&nbsp;<strong>two visiting card.</strong><br />\r\n<strong><u>Please note:</u></strong>&nbsp;Photograph should not be more than 3 months old, scanned/stapled and should not be used in any of the previous visas.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>8. Financial:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Foreign exchange endorsement or copy of credit card or Bank Statement for last 6 months.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>9. Note Verbal:&nbsp;</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Note verbal is required for official or diplomatic passport holder<strong>.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Special Note: In all above visa category, an Immigration Clearance letter is required from Mongolia. any person or hotel manager or tour company can arrange with booking confirmation and minimal charge.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size:20px\">for more information :&nbsp;https://visathing.com/country/mongolia/</span></strong></p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-20', 1),
