(151, 'Mozambique', 'MOZ', 'mz.png', '<h4>&nbsp;Basic information</h4>\r\n\r\n<h5>&nbsp;</h5>\r\n\r\n<h2>&nbsp;Check List</h2>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>GENERAL REQUIREMENTS:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Submit an original passport, valid for at least 6 months from the date of entry into Mozambique and with at least 1 blank page for a visa. Amendment pages are excluded.</li>\r\n	<li>Citizens other than from the United States of America and Canada, but living in these countries, must submit a copy of their permanent residence status.</li>\r\n	<li>Fill the visa application form properly. It is very important that you provide all the information required, including the name and address of your place of stay in Mozambique. Please be advised that lack of information may result in delay or even denial of your application.</li>\r\n	<li>Submit 2 copies of passport size photographs.</li>\r\n	<li>Visitors are required to hold proof of sufficient funds to cover their stay and documents required for their next destination.</li>\r\n	<li>Sufficient funds to support their stay and proof of purpose of visit. Extension of a further 30 days is possible.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px\">for more information plz :&nbsp;https://visathing.com/country/mozambique/</span></p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-22', 1),
(152, 'Myanmar [Burma]', 'MMR', 'mm.png', '<h4>&nbsp;Basic information</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Myanmar opened counselor office at Dhaka on 26 March 1951. After Bangladesh got the independent from East Pakistan on 16 December 1971, Myanmar and Bangladesh have close and cordial ties since the founding of Bangladesh in 1972. On 13 January 1972, Myanmar accorded recognition to Bangladesh. Myanmar was one of the first countries to recognize Bangladesh. The two countries established diplomatic relations at Embassy level on 21 March 1972.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>&nbsp;Fees &amp; Processing Time</h4>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Visa Processing Fee</strong>&nbsp;for Complete Application (As Per Check List):</p>\r\n\r\n<table style=\"width:371px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><strong>Visa &amp; Application Center Fee&nbsp;</strong>(BDT)</td>\r\n			<td><strong>VISAThing Express Fee&nbsp;</strong>(BDT)</td>\r\n			<td><strong>Total&nbsp;</strong>(BDT)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>7500/- (Express Service)</td>\r\n			<td>700/-</td>\r\n			<td>8200/-</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>10000/- (Super Express Service)</td>\r\n			<td>700/-</td>\r\n			<td>10700/-</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Processing Time:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Express Service: Total processing&nbsp;time is 3 working days.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Super Express Service: Total processing time is 1 working day.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>&nbsp;Check List</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Tourist / Business Visa Requirements:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1. Passport:&nbsp;</strong>Original Passport with validity of minimum six months after the intended date of departure and minimum two blank pages for visa stamp.<br />\r\n<strong>a)&nbsp;</strong>Copy of previous passports and visas issued.<br />\r\n<strong>b)</strong>&nbsp;Attach all your old passports (if any).<br />\r\n<strong>c)</strong>&nbsp;If any visa request was refused, details of original letter issued by the authorities of that country would be preferred.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2. NID copy</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>3. Myanmar Visa Application Form:&nbsp;</strong>Visa application form must be filled and signed by the applicant.&nbsp;<a href=\"https://arnimholidays.com/myanmar_business_visa_application_form.pdf\">Click Here</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>4. Photo Specification:&nbsp;</strong>Two recent passport size photographs with matt or semi matt finish, white background and without border&nbsp;<strong>(Size: 35mm x 45mm)</strong><br />\r\nPlease Note:&nbsp;Photograph should not be more than 3 months old, scanned/stapled and should not be used in any of the previous visas.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>5. Invitation Letter:&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>Required for business visa. And Myanmar company registration certificate.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>6. Forwarding-Letter:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; a)&nbsp;</strong>Forwarding Letter / NOC from the applicant&rsquo;s company authority on the company&rsquo;s letter head stating applicant&rsquo;s name, designation, passport number, purpose and duration of visit.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;b)&nbsp;</strong>Visa request letter&nbsp;from the educational institute or student card/evidence of school enrollment (if student)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>7. Proof of Occupation:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>a)&nbsp;</strong>Company registration certificate&nbsp;(original notarized English translated and photocopy of the original) if the applicant is a first time traveler or a proprietor.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>b)&nbsp;</strong>Office ID card copy&nbsp;&amp; Visiting cards.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>8. Financials:</strong><br />\r\n<strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; a)&nbsp;</strong>Company&rsquo;s or Personal Bank Statement for last six months mentioning the Bank&rsquo;s name, Bank&rsquo;s Telephone Number clearly.<br />\r\n<strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; b)</strong>&nbsp;Salary slip for the last six months. (If Any)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>9. Airline &amp; Hotel Reservation:&nbsp;</strong>Ticket Itinerary &amp; Hotel Booking.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px\">for more information :&nbsp;https://visathing.com/country/myanmar/</span></p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-22', 1),
(153, 'Namibia', 'NAM', 'na.png', '<p><span style=\"font-size:22px\">&nbsp;for all information please click here : https://stickervisa.com/namibia/</span></p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-22', 1),
(154, 'Nauru', 'NRU', 'nr.png', '<h1>Nauru Visa From Bangladesh<br />\r\n<a href=\"https://visathing.com/continent/oceania/\" rel=\"tag\">Oceania</a></h1>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>&nbsp;Check List</h2>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>1. Passport :</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>A clear colour copy of the information page(s) from the applicant&rsquo;s passport. The passport must:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>a</strong>. Be valid for six months beyond entry date</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>b</strong>. Have at least two blank visa pages</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>2. Proof of Travel Arrangements:&nbsp;</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Details of travel arrangements. These&nbsp;must be provided as:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>a</strong>. A copy of a return e-ticket from Nauru Airlines showing exact entry and exit dates</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>b</strong>. Proof of a confirmed hotel confirmation with one of the following hotels</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>c</strong>. If residing with a friend or relative, a supporting letter/email to confirm</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>3. Letter of Support:&nbsp;</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>A Letter of Introduction&nbsp;which must include:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>a</strong>. Name of applicant(s)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>b</strong>. Passport number(s) of applicant(s)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>c</strong>. Purpose of the trip</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>d</strong>. Date of expected travel</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>e</strong>. Date of expected departure</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>f</strong>. this letter must be signed and dated</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>4. Visa Application Form:&nbsp;</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>One fully completed and signed application form.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:22px\">for more information :&nbsp;https://visathing.com/country/nauru/</span></p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-22', 1);
