(164, 'North Korea', 'PRK', 'kp.png', '<h3>Student Visa</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Who can apply</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>An individual who is a regular student or student seeking admission/researcher in any government-approved educational institution in Bangladesh, he /she is eligible to apply for Student visa.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>&nbsp;</strong><strong>Duration of student visa</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;A student visa may be issued for a maximum period of one (01) year with multiple entries. The duration of stay in this category is as required in each visit.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>&nbsp;</strong><strong>Extension of visa</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Visa may be further extended from Bangladesh. Extension up to the course tenure could be obtained from Department of Immigration and Passport (DIP) in Bangladesh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Please note that the validity of the visa begins from the date of issue and not from the date of travel on your application form.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Student&nbsp;visa (S): (Multiple entry) &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Visa Fee: KRW 60,000</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>  (S): ( )</p>\r\n\r\n<table style=\"width:1053px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>SL No</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Visa requirements</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Visa requirements (Korean Language)</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>01</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>MRV/Visa Application form fill up online&nbsp; (<a href=\"https://www.visa.gov.bd/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">www.visa.gov.bd</a>)</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>MRV /&nbsp;</strong><strong></strong>&nbsp;<strong></strong>&nbsp;<strong></strong>&nbsp;<strong></strong>&nbsp;<strong></strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>02</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Two Passport size colour photo</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong></strong>&nbsp;<strong></strong>&nbsp;<strong></strong>&nbsp;<strong></strong>&nbsp;<strong></strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>03</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Certification of Admission</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong></strong>&nbsp;<strong></strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>04</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>School&rsquo;s/College/University recommendation for visa issuance</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong></strong><strong>&nbsp;/&nbsp;</strong><strong></strong><strong>&nbsp;/&nbsp;</strong><strong></strong>&nbsp;<strong></strong>&nbsp;<strong></strong>&nbsp;<strong></strong><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>05</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Payment slip (initial payment amount)</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong></strong>&nbsp;<strong></strong><strong>&nbsp;(</strong><strong></strong>&nbsp;<strong></strong>&nbsp;<strong></strong><strong>)</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>06</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Copy of school/collage/university registration</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong></strong><strong>&nbsp;/&nbsp;</strong><strong></strong><strong>&nbsp;/&nbsp;</strong><strong></strong>&nbsp;<strong></strong>&nbsp;<strong></strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>07</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Guarantee letter</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong></strong>&nbsp;<strong></strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>08</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Copy of identification of the Guarantor</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong></strong>&nbsp;<strong></strong>&nbsp;<strong></strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>09</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Copy of identification of the Guarantor</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong></strong>&nbsp;<strong></strong>&nbsp;<strong></strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>10</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Certificate of bank guarantor of the guarantor</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong></strong>&nbsp;<strong></strong>&nbsp;<strong></strong>&nbsp;<strong></strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>11</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong>Passport copy</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p><strong></strong>&nbsp;<strong></strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong>Visa fees are determined on the basis of reciprocity with the country of the foreign national seeking visa. Please note that the visa fee is non-refundable, even if the visa is denied or the visa application is withdrawn.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong><u>Consular Service by post</u></strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The Embassy of Bangladesh in Seoul provides consular services by post. You may send your visa application by post along with passport and all other required documents including a prepaid postal envelope with self-address, clearly written on top of the envelope.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In order to receive a visa by post, you must pay the visa fee by a postal order or bank draft in favour of the following:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&lsquo;Bangladesh Embassy, Seoul&rsquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px\">for more information :&nbsp;http://bdembassykorea.org/en/?page_id=1299</span></p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-22', 1),
(165, 'Northern Mariana Islands', 'MNP', 'mp.png', '<p><span style=\"font-size:24px\">for more information plese click here : https://www.traveldocs.com/expedited-visa-services/north-mariana-islands-visa-processing-country164&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-22', 1),
(166, 'Norway', 'NOR', 'no.png', '<p><strong>Study in Norway from Bangladesh:</strong><br />\r\nEducation in Norway offers the benefits of a modern university system which has an international reputation for high quality studies. Located<br />\r\nbetween western and eastern Europe, the country of Norway has unspoiled natural resources and an interesting historical and cultural heritage.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Bachelor Program</strong>: Every student at least 13 years study has to be completed (HSC+ One year<br />\r\ncompletion certificate from any Bangladeshi University), Diploma also apply bachelor program.<br />\r\nStudy gap maximum 5 years is accepted and Madrasa Education is allowed. HSC result not be<br />\r\nbelow GPA 4.50/5.00 and IELTS score not be below overall 6.5<br />\r\nMasters Program: At least bachelor Pass (Hons. BSc, BBA, BA). Study gap maximum 4 years.<br />\r\nBachelor result not be below CGPA 3.25 or 75% marks and IELTS score not be below overall 6.0<br />\r\nLanguage Proficiency: IELTS score of 6.5 (At least) required. Some universities take student by<br />\r\nIELTS: 6.0.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>Required Documents for Admission:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Passport valid for at least six months.</li>\r\n	<li>Recent Passport size photo.</li>\r\n	<li>SSC, HSC &amp; Bachelor Certificate &amp; Transcript</li>\r\n	<li>IELTS Certificate (IELTS Score 6.0/6.5)</li>\r\n	<li>Statement of purpose/Letter of Intent</li>\r\n	<li>Two Recommendation Letter (for Masters)</li>\r\n	<li>CV (docx file)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Proof of financial ability: For student&rsquo;s safety and surviving in Norway, Every student needs to<br />\r\nblock NOK 106000 in his personal account in Norwegian Bank. In equivalent in BDT 10,88,070.86/-<br />\r\n(Conversion rate was NOK 1=BDT 10.26 The values are standardized by the International Money<br />\r\nExchange Values) which is very affordable and manageable for Bangladeshi students.<br />\r\nWork facilities: According to the Norwegian law any student can work 120 full days or 240 half<br />\r\ndays per year within his study period and 1 day= 8 hours, 1 hour=8.51 euro minimum salary. So<br />\r\nfor BD student it is very easy to manage living cost through student job or mini job.<br />\r\nAfter Study: If any student finished his study successfully then get 18 months extra time for job<br />\r\nsearching, it is called job searching period. Norway has lowest unemployment rate in the world so<br />\r\nit should be easy to get good job then rest of the world.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nPlease call 01958-666999 &amp; 01958-666900 for more information.</p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2018-12-23', 1),
