(173, 'Paraguay', 'PRY', 'py.png', '<h4>&nbsp;Basic information</h4>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>For Paraguay, VISAThing provides</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.0.0/svg/2714.svg\" />&nbsp;Logistics support</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>&nbsp;Visa Consultancy</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There is no Embassy or Consulate office of Paraguay in Dhaka, one can get more information from nearest Paraguay Embassy which is in India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>EMBASSY OF PARAGUAY</strong>:<br />\r\nB&ndash;11, Vasant Marg, Vasant Vihar,<br />\r\nNew Delhi &ndash; 110057.<br />\r\n<strong>Tel:</strong>&nbsp;(+91) 11 4270 5676<br />\r\n<strong>Fax</strong>: (+91) 11 4270 5672<br />\r\nWebsite:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.paraguayembassy.in/\">http://www.paraguayembassy.in</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>While applying in the Paraguay Embassy, an applicant needs to attend there in person. However, if the applicant is able to provide reasonable justification toward the Embassy of Paraguay in New Delhi, he/she can apply through a third party upon the permission granted by the embassy or consular section. Also, if the inviter can justify properly regarding applicant&rsquo;s position of being unable to travel India for visa application, the embassy may provide a permission to apply through an agent.&nbsp;<strong>Only on such case, VisaThing is able to provide visa logistics / processing support (Logistics charge applicable).</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<h4>&nbsp;Ground Support</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Now visa application lodgment in India is easier &amp; hassle free with&nbsp;<strong>VISAThing&rsquo;s Ground Support</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Why Do You Need</strong>&nbsp;<strong>VISAThing&rsquo;s Ground Support</strong>?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some countries having embassies located in India requires personal presence of the visa applicant at the Embassy/VFS for in person interview or biometric data collection. The applicant must visit the embassy in India to submit the visa application.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Most of the applicants face difficulty in</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>preparing an error visa application with all the necessary documents</li>\r\n	<li>the submission procedures at the embassy</li>\r\n	<li>navigating through the city and finding suitable lodging&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.visathing.com/ground-support/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">&hellip;Read more</a></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h2>&nbsp;Check List</h2>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong><u>TOURIST VISA REQUIREMENT:</u></strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>1. Two VISA Application Forms fully completed (filled electronically) and signed by the applicant. Photocopies of the filled application will not be accepted.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Three recent passport-size color photographs, with white background.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Two color photocopies of the Passport (1, 2 and last page). Passport should have minimum validity of&nbsp;<u>one year&nbsp;</u>from the intended date of entry into Paraguay.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. Original of police Record / Clearance Certificate, duly notarized and legalized by the Ministry. (Valid for six months).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5, Round- trip tickets, the travel itinerary, in advance, (with Hotel bookings).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>6. Invitation Letter from Paraguay (The Invitee company has to present the original invitation to the Paraguay Ministry (MRE-Passport office) and get it attested &amp; submit the same along with the application at the Embassy of Paraguay in New Delhi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>7. Proof of economic solvency. Original Bank statement, from last 3 months and copy of credit card.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>8. Application must be submitted in 20 days in advance in the Embassy.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong><u>BUSINESS VISA REQUIREMENT:</u></strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>1. Two VISA Application Forms fully completed (filled electronically) and signed by the applicant. Photocopies of the filled application will not be accepted.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Three recent passport-size color photographs, with white background.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Two color photocopies of the Passport (1, 2 and last page). Passport should have minimum validity of one year from the intended date of entry into Paraguay.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. Original of police Record / Clearance Certificate, duly notarized and legalized by the Ministry of External Affairs of the Government of your country (valid for six months).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5. Round- trip tickets, the travel itinerary, in advance, (with Hotel bookings).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>6. Invitation Letter from Paraguay (The Invitee company has to&nbsp; present the original invitation to the Paraguay Ministry (MRE-Passport office) and get it attested &amp; submit the same along with the application at the Embassy of Paraguay in New Delhi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>7. Valid Registration paper from the Bangladeshi Merchants Chamber or Chamber of Commerce &amp; Valid copy of Company Registration.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>8. Proof of economic solvency. Original Bank statement, from last 3 months and copy of credit card.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>9. Application must be submitted in 20 days in advance in the Embassy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><u>Besides these, Bangladeshi Nations have to fulfill the following:</u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>It is required to attach a copy of the valid Trade License, or similar paper duly legalized by Merchants Chamber or Chamber of Commerce and the Ministry of External Affairs of the country where document has been originated.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Police Clearance Certificate duly notarized and attested by the Ministry of External Affairs if it is a country&rsquo;s requirement.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px\">for more information :&nbsp;https://visathing.com/country/paraguay/</span></p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-23', 1),
(174, 'Peru', 'PER', 'pe.png', '<p><span style=\"font-size:20px\">for all information please lick here :&nbsp;http://stickervisa.com/peru/#:~:text=Valid%20passport%20for%20at%20least,size%20between%2070%25%20%E2%80%93%2080%25)</span></p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-23', 1),
(175, 'Philippines', 'PHL', 'ph.png', '<h3>RESS RELEASES</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://dhakape.dfa.gov.ph/embassy-news/651-ph-embassy-meets-with-youth-opportunities-coo\">PH Embassy meets with Youth Opportunities COO</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://dhakape.dfa.gov.ph/embassy-news/651-ph-embassy-meets-with-youth-opportunities-coo\"><img alt=\"article thumbnail\" src=\"https://dhakape.dfa.gov.ph/images/2020/youth_opportunies_COO_lnd_thumb.jpg\" style=\"float:left; height:64px; width:64px\" /></a>PH Embassy meets with Youth Opportunities COO &nbsp; 3 December 2020, Dhaka &ndash; PH Embassy met with Mr. Osama Bin Noor, Co-founder and Chief Operating Officer of Youth Opportunities, an award-winning...</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://dhakape.dfa.gov.ph/embassy-news/647-philippine-embassy-in-bangladesh-receives-the-php-group\">Philippine Embassy in Bangladesh receives The PHP Group</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://dhakape.dfa.gov.ph/embassy-news/611-launch-of-philippine-humanitarian-assistance-registry-website\">Launch of Philippine Humanitarian Assistance Registry Website</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://dhakape.dfa.gov.ph/embassy-news/609-special-free-screening-of-zarzuela-walang-sugat\">Special Free Screening of Zarzuela, &ldquo;Walang Sugat&rdquo;</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://dhakape.dfa.gov.ph/embassy-news/557-philippine-embassy-in-bangladesh-repatriates-filipinos-in-maldives\">Philippine Embassy in Bangladesh Repatriates Filipinos in Maldives</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>More in</strong><a href=\"https://dhakape.dfa.gov.ph/embassy-news\">Press Releases</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Nationals from countries in the LIST who are traveling to the Philippines for business and tourism purposes are allowed to enter the Philippines without visas for a stay not exceeding thirty (30) days, provided they hold valid tickets for their return journey to port of origin or next port of destination and their passports valid for a period of at least six (6) months beyond the contemplated period of stay.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nThe following are allowed to enter the Philippines without a visa for a stay&nbsp;<strong>NOT exceeding fourteen (14) days:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n1.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Holders of Hong Kong Special Administrative (SAR) passports.<br />\r\n2.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Holders of Macau Special Administrative Region (SAR) passports.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nThe following are allowed to enter the Philippines without a visa for a stay NOT exceeding seven (7) days:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n1.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Holders of Macau-Portuguese passports.<br />\r\n2.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Holders of Hong Kong British passports.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>Important Note</strong>: Nationals who are subjects of deportation/blacklist orders of the Department and the Bureau of Immigration shall not be admitted to the Philippines. Further inquiries may be addressed to the Philippine Embassy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>VISA REQUIRMENTS</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>FOR HOLDERS OF DIPLOMATIC AND OFFICIAL PASSPORT/GOVERNMENT OFFICIAL GOING TO THE PHILIPPINES:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n1.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Accomplished Application for Philippine Visa form (click here to download the form)<br />\r\n2.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Note Verbal from the Ministry of Foreign Affairs<br />\r\n3.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Passport valid for not less than six(6) months after sojourn in the Philippines<br />\r\n4.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Two copies of 2&Prime; x 2&Prime; recent photographs<br />\r\n5.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Visa fee: GRATIS</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>FOR BANGLADESHI NATIONALS - HOLDERS OF DIPLOMATIC AND OFFICIAL PASSPORTS</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Bangladeshi nationals who are holders of valid diplomatic or special passports may enter the Philippines without entry visas and stay for a period of thirty (30) days.</li>\r\n	<li>Bangladeshi nationals who are holders of valid diplomatic or special passports on assigment in the Philippines may stay without visas for entry only for a period of thirty (30) days and required to obtain appropriate 9(e)&nbsp; visa and other necessary accreditation from the DFA within thirty (30) days.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>VISA APPLICATION PROCEDURE</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>Submission of Documents</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><br />\r\n1.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Visa applications will be accepted at Gate No. 2 strictly from 9:00AM-11:30AM (0900H-1130H) only.<br />\r\n2.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Visa applicants shall submit relevant documents through accredited agencies only.<br />\r\n3.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Processing fee payment of BDT3,400 shall also be made through these accredited agencies.<br />\r\n4.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;The accredited agencies will receive the corresponding receipt for the payment and will get notice to wait for a call from the Embassy if an application is approved or not and if a schedule for interview is necessary.<br />\r\n5.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;No foreign nationals or walk-in applicants may enter the premises at any time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>Interview of Visa Applicants</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n1.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;If an interview is necessary, a visa applicant will receive a call from the Embassy within five (5) working days after submission of the application and will be informed of the date and time of the interview.<br />\r\n2.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;On the scheduled interview, the visa applicant shall proceed to Gate No. 1 and shall bring the following:<br />\r\na.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Valid ID to be presented to the guard<br />\r\nb.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Documents needed for the interview<br />\r\n3.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;No applicant shall be allowed to bring a bag inside the premises.<br />\r\n4.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;The applicant shall be escorted by the guard to leave the premises after the interview.<br />\r\nApproved Visa Application<br />\r\n1.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;If a visa application is approved, the accredited agency will receive a call from the Embassy on the sixth (6th) working day from the submission of documents and will be given a schedule for submission of passport.<br />\r\n2.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;The accredited agency&rsquo;s representative shall proceed to Gate No. 2 for the submission of passport strictly from 9:00AM-12:00NN (0900H-1200H) only.<br />\r\n3.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;The accredited agency shall be given a stub with a schedule for the release of the visa.<br />\r\nRelease of Visa<br />\r\n1.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Release of the visa is at Gate No. 2 strictly from 2:00PM to 4:00PM (1400H-1600H) only.<br />\r\n2.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;The accredited agency shall present the stub and receipt to the Embassy staff in claiming the visa at the gate.<br />\r\n3.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Under no circumstance shall the guard or consular staff open the gate.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>FOR HOLDERS OF ORDINARY PASSPORTS TO STUDY IN THE PHILIPPINES</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>1.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Accomplished Application for Visa form<br />\r\n2.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Prospective foreign students shall communicate directly with the school in the Philippines and comply with the school&rsquo;s institutional requirements, which shall include the submission of the following documents:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\na.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Five (5) copies of the Student&rsquo;s Personal History duly signed by him/her, both in English and in national alphabet accompanied by his/her personal seal, if any, and containing, among others his/her left and right thumbprints and a 2&times;2 photograph on plain white background taken not more than six (6) months prior to submission.<br />\r\nb.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;A notarized affidavit of support including bank statements or notarized notice of grant for institutional scholars to cover expenses for the students accommodation and subsistence, as well as school dues and other incidental expenses.<br />\r\nc.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Transcript of Records/Scholastic Records duly authenticated by the Philippine Embassy/Consulate located in the student applicant&rsquo;s country of origin or legal residence.<br />\r\nd.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Photocopy of data page of the student&rsquo;s passport showing date and place of birth, and birth certificate or its equivalent by the Philippine Embassy/Consulate.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n3.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;The school, satisfied with the student&rsquo;s compliance with its requirements, shall issue a Notice of Acceptance (NOA) to the student and submit a duplicate copy thereof to the Department of Foreign Affairs, together with a certified true copy of the Commission on Higher Education&rsquo;s Certificate of Eligibility of Admission, when necessary, and the above-cited document-requirements. These documents shall be hand carried to the DFA by the School&rsquo;s designated liaison officer under a cover letter on the school&rsquo;s official stationary signed by the school registrar and stamped with the school&rsquo;s dry seal requesting that a student visa be issued to the person named therein.<br />\r\n4.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;The DFA shall endorse the documents to the Philippine Embassy/Consulate located in the prospective student&rsquo;s country of origin or place of legal residence, regardless of where the prospective student is at the time of application.<br />\r\n5.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;The concerned Philippine Embassy/Consulate shall notify in writing the student of the receipt of the documents and require him/her to appear in person before a Consular Officer for interview and compliance with consular requirements. In addition to the documents transmitted to the Embassy/Consulate by the DFA, the following requirements shall be submitted by the student to the Consular Officer:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\na.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Original of the school&rsquo;s Notice of Admission (NOA) containing a clear impression of the school&rsquo;s dry seal;<br />\r\nb.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Original of the Certificate of Admission of Eligibility (CEA) issued by the CHED if enrolled in courses or programs where restrictions may exist due to shortage of facilities, as in Medicine or Dentistry;<br />\r\nc.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Police clearance issued by the national police authorities in the student&rsquo;s country of origin or legal residence, authenticated by the Philippine Embassy/Consulate having consular jurisdiction over the place;<br />\r\nd.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Medical health certificate issued by an authorized physician including, but not limited to, standard-size chest x-ray, Hepatitis B clearance; and<br />\r\nThe Student visa processing fee of Tk 21,250.00</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n6.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;The consular officer shall not assume the task of determining the student&rsquo;s scholastic fitness for the program applied for and shall issue the student visa as soon as the requirements are accomplished.<br />\r\n7.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;A notice of visa issuance shall be furnished by the DFA to the school, the CHED, BI and NBI and the NICA as soon as it receives report of this effect from the issuing Embassy/Consulate.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nPlease click on the following to visit these helpful links:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Commission on Higher Education (CHED)<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Bureau of Immigration (BI)<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>FOR SEAMAN</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n1.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Letter from the manning agency addressed to the Embassy<br />\r\n2.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Photocopy of Seaman&rsquo;s Book<br />\r\n3.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Passport valid for not less than six(6) months after sojourn in the Philippines<br />\r\n4.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Two copies of 2&Prime; x 2&Prime; recent photographs<br />\r\n5.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Visa fee of Tk 1,700.00</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>VISA PROCESSING TIME</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Application for visa is open from 9:00 am to 12:00 nn only<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Schedule of release of available visas is from 1:00 pm to 4:00 pm<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;It takes ten to fifteen (10-15) working days before a visa is issued</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:22px\">for all information please click :&nbsp;https://dhakape.dfa.gov.ph/93-visa</span></p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-23', 1),
