(180, 'Qatar', 'QAT', 'qa.png', '<p><a href=\"https://travelvisaworld.com/category/bangladesh/\" rel=\"category tag\">BANGLADESH</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h1>Qatar Visa Information for Bangladeshi Passport Holders, How to Apply &amp; Travel Requirements</h1>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"Qatar | Qatar visa information for Bangladeshi \" src=\"https://lonelyplanetwp.imgix.net/2019/02/qatar3000-64e1dc05f14d.jpg?crop=entropy&amp;fit=crop&amp;h=421&amp;sharp=10&amp;vib=20&amp;w=748\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Qatar is one of the fastest-growing developed countries with fun places to visit such as the Souq Waqif or &ldquo;Standing Market&rdquo;, the Sheikh Faisal Bin Qassim Al Thani Museum, and the 300-metre tall skyscraper known as the Aspire Tower.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Qatar also has a great many economic and educational opportunities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Summary of Visa Content</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Qatar Visa Types, Processing Time &amp; Duration</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Show&nbsp;<select name=\"tablepress-36_length\"><option value=\"10\">10</option><option value=\"25\">25</option><option value=\"50\">50</option><option value=\"100\">100</option></select>&nbsp;entries</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Search:<input type=\"search\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<table id=\"tablepress-36\">\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\">Visa Type</th>\r\n			<th colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\">Processing Time</th>\r\n			<th colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\">Duration of Stay</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Business Visa</td>\r\n			<td>4-15 days</td>\r\n			<td>90 days</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Tourist Visa</td>\r\n			<td>4-15 days</td>\r\n			<td>30 days</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Student Visa</td>\r\n			<td>4-15 days</td>\r\n			<td>Determined by academic program</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Family Visa</td>\r\n			<td>4-15 days</td>\r\n			<td>6 months - 5 years</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>Showing 1 to 4 of 4 entries</p>\r\n\r\n<p>PreviousNext</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>General Requirements for a Qatar Visa</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Properly filled Qatar visa application form</li>\r\n	<li>An international passport with a validity period of no less than 60 days after the visa expires and 2 empty pages for endorsements</li>\r\n	<li>2 coloured passport size photographs taken with a white background</li>\r\n	<li>2 copies of the first passport pages</li>\r\n	<li>Proof of visa application fee payment</li>\r\n	<li>Bank statements for the last 3 months</li>\r\n	<li>Confirmed hotel reservation or travel itinerary</li>\r\n	<li>Health certificate form assigned by a medical clinic in Bangladesh</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Qatar Business Visa</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>This visa is issued to Bangladeshi seeking to carry out business in Qatar.</li>\r\n	<li>There are 3 types which are:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>72-hour business visa: It is granted on arrival in Qatar and has a 72-hour visa extension. It is suitable for Bangladeshis on short business trips such as client meetings.</li>\r\n		<li>Business visa: It is applied to carry out contractual work for a period of 3 months. The employer of an approved Qatari company is to prepare this visa.</li>\r\n		<li>Investor Visa: It is for Bangladeshis seeking investment opportunities in Qatar. Authentic documents affirming ownership of property is needed to receive this visa.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Qatar Tourist Visa</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>This visa type is for Bangladeshis who wish to visit Qatar for tourist purposes.</li>\r\n	<li>To be granted this visa applicant must prove that the purpose of the visit is temporary</li>\r\n	<li>This visa extendable for visa waiver countries only. Bangladeshis are to request a new visa.</li>\r\n	<li>This visa cannot be used to seek employment in Qatar</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Qatar Student Visa</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>This visa is issued to Bangladeshis who wish to study in Qatar</li>\r\n	<li>In addition to the general requirements, student visa applicants should have:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>A confirmed admission letter from the school</li>\r\n		<li>A copy of the passport of the financial sponsor</li>\r\n		<li>Academic documents such as original copies of school transcripts</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Qatar Family Visa</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>This visa is divided into:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Family Resident Visa: It is for family members of a Qatar national or permanent residence visa holder seeking permanent residence in Qatar. This visa can be renewed for a period of 1 to 5 years.</li>\r\n		<li>Family Visit Visa: It is for family members of a Qatar national or permanent residence visa holder seeking temporary residence in Qatar.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>Family Resident visa applicants must also possess:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Certificates of attestation for birth or marriage from a Bangladesh embassy and Ministry of Foreign Affairs (MOFA) in Qatar</li>\r\n		<li>A copy of the latest educational certificate</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Qatar Visa Fees</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Show&nbsp;<select name=\"tablepress-37_length\"><option value=\"10\">10</option><option value=\"25\">25</option><option value=\"50\">50</option><option value=\"100\">100</option></select>&nbsp;entries</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Search:<input type=\"search\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<table id=\"tablepress-37\">\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\">Visa Types</th>\r\n			<th colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\">Visa Fee (QAR)</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Tourist Visa</td>\r\n			<td>50</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Family Visa</td>\r\n			<td>200</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>Showing 1 to 2 of 2 entries</p>\r\n\r\n<p>PreviousNext</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Qatar Visa Application Centre in Bangladesh</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Show&nbsp;<select name=\"tablepress-41_length\"><option value=\"10\">10</option><option value=\"25\">25</option><option value=\"50\">50</option><option value=\"100\">100</option></select>&nbsp;entries</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Search:<input type=\"search\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<table id=\"tablepress-41\">\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\">Location</th>\r\n			<th colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\">Address</th>\r\n			<th colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\">Phone number</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Dhaka</td>\r\n			<td>House No. 1, Road<br />\r\n			No. 79/81<br />\r\n			Gulshan No. 2<br />\r\n			Dhaka 1212<br />\r\n			Bangladesh</td>\r\n			<td>(+880) 2 988 7429<br />\r\n			(+880) 2 881 9930</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>Showing 1 to 1 of 1 entries</p>\r\n\r\n<p>PreviousNext</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Commonly Asked Questions about Qatar Visa</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>Can changes be made to my visa application after submission?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>No. Once a visa application has been submitted, changes cannot be made. Reapplication will be needed to do if necessary.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Can the status of my visa application be checked?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Yes. The status of visa application can be checked after submission of application.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Do Bangladeshis qualify for Qatar visa on arrival?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>No. Bangladeshis currently is not a part of the 80 visa waiver countries allowed for visa on arrival in Qatar</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>If my visa does not get approved can my service fee be refunded</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>No. Service fee is non-refundable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:22px\">for more information please click here :&nbsp;https://travelvisaworld.com/bangladesh/qatar-visa-information-and-travel-requirements-for-bangladeshis/</span></p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-23', 1),
(181, 'Republic of the Congo', 'COG', 'cg.png', '<p><span style=\"font-size:20px\">&nbsp;for more information please click here : http://stickervisa.com/congo/</span></p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-23', 1),
(182, 'Reunion', 'REU', 're.png', '<h1>Visa and entry</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Image information01.12.2017 - Article</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Information about visa applications&nbsp;(short- and long-term stay)&nbsp;in Germany</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Info</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Bangladeshi nationals or non-EU&nbsp;nationals need a visa in order to enter Germany.</strong><br />\r\nThe type of visa you require depends on how long you plan to stay. Are you planning a short visit to Germany, e.g. for a holiday? Or would you like to stay longer, e.g. to attend university? Please click on the descriptions below to find more information about the visa you require for your trip to Germany.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><strong><strong>All Visa Applicants (both short-&nbsp;and long-term)&nbsp;should fill up the&nbsp; &ldquo;Declaration of Consent&rdquo;, sign it and submit it with the visa application. Please download it&nbsp;from here:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://dhaka.diplo.de/blob/2157316/34924dbefb3d20b70937b207f829bb27/declaration-of-consent-data.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Declaration of Consent\">Declaration of Consent</a></strong></strong></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Short stay&nbsp;</strong>(less than 90 days):</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://dhaka.diplo.de/bd-en/service/visa-einreise/-/1976522\" target=\"_self\" title=\"Schengen visa\">Schengen Visa</a>&nbsp;(for business, trade fair, tourism, transit, medical etc. maximum of 90 days)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Important:&nbsp;</strong><a href=\"https://dhaka.diplo.de/blob/2221194/5d491dfc34caefdbe93ab806287514fc/datenschutz-info-data.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"General Data Protection Regulation\">General Data Protection Regulation</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>PLEASE NOTE:</strong>&nbsp;the ONLINE visa application form will reduce the amount of time an applicant has to spend at the visa counter. After the visa application form has been filled-in online, it has to be printed, therefore a printer&nbsp;must&nbsp;be attached to the computer. When the application is printed, a barcode is generated and printed automatically on the application form. On the other hand, the visa application form in pdf format can also be downloaded and&nbsp;filled-in (also by hand), but it will cost the applicant longer time at the visa counter.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Long stay&nbsp;</strong>(more than 90 days):</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>(e.g. to attend university, work or join a family member in Germany)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Student Visa</strong>: For students who have been accepted by a college in Germany. See&nbsp;<a href=\"https://dhaka.diplo.de/blob/2130280/d1287dfa3206e6af5280b57651c59ce9/2021-checklist-studenten-data.pdf\" target=\"_self\" title=\"Checklist Student Visa\">this checklist</a>for your Student Visa application.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Family Reunion Visa</strong>: To join your spouse living in Germany you have to file an application for&nbsp;<a href=\"https://dhaka.diplo.de/blob/2076250/bc3fa65320f5bf5f06501d055951aa96/fz-data.pdf\" target=\"_self\" title=\"Family Reunion Visa\">Family reunion</a>&nbsp;or for&nbsp;<a href=\"https://dhaka.diplo.de/blob/2182106/cbbffa804353811dc6a4d864fd2765bb/intended-marriage-data.pdf\" target=\"_self\" title=\"Intended Marriage\">Intended marriage</a>&nbsp;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Family Reunion with&nbsp;EU/EEA citizen</strong>: If your spouse living in Germany possesses an&nbsp;EU/ EEA citizenship different requirements apply to your&nbsp;<a href=\"https://dhaka.diplo.de/blob/2076262/1c73f2411c6a5a8eaf13f53c8f2fa754/eu-fz-eea-2017-data.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Family Reunion with an EU/EEA Citizen\">Family Reunion with&nbsp;EU/EEA citizen application</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Employment</strong>: If you have found a Job in Germany, you need to apply for a visa for employment. Please write an email to the visa section for details.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://videx-national.diplo.de/videx/visum-erfassung/#/videx-langfristiger-aufenthalt\" target=\"_blank\">Long-term visa application form</a>&nbsp;(ONLINE)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://dhaka.diplo.de/blob/2081380/d7f0cecc3a5d78522cf3c035d2942c62/antrag-d-visa-data.pdf\" target=\"_self\" title=\"Long-term Visa (student, family reunion etc.) visa application form\">Long-term&nbsp;visa application form</a>&nbsp;(pdf)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Important:</strong>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://dhaka.diplo.de/blob/2221194/5d491dfc34caefdbe93ab806287514fc/datenschutz-info-data.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"General Data Protection Regulation\">General Data Protection Regulation</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>As of 1 August 2018, close family members (spouses,&nbsp;unmarried minor children and parents of minor children) of a person eligible for subsidiary protection in Germany will be able to apply for a visa for the purpose of family reunion. Eligible family members may already register for an appointment to submit their visa application&nbsp;<a href=\"https://service2.diplo.de/rktermin/extern/choose_realmList.do?request_locale=de&amp;locationCode=subs\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Telephone queries:</strong>&nbsp;The Visa Section can be contacted through the Embassy&#39;s telephone number +880 2 5566 8650 during week-days between 2.30 p.m. and 3.30 p.m. (Bangladesh&nbsp;time).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px\">for more information :&nbsp;https://dhaka.diplo.de/bd-en/service/visa-einreise/-/1976508</span></p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-23', 1),
(183, 'Romania', 'ROU', 'ro.png', '<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n\r\n<h1>Romania Student Visa from Bangladesh</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>Basic Information</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Important Visa Information:</strong><br />\r\nAs there no Embassy or Consulate of Romania in Bangladesh, so that documents must be submitted to the nearest Embassy of Romania in New Delhi, India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Application Can be Submitted here from Bangladesh:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>VISAThing for Student</strong><br />\r\n1st Floor, Homestead Gulshan Link Tower, Gulshan-Badda Link Road, Gulshan-1, Dhaka-1212<br />\r\nPhone: (+88) 0196 777 7788 (Hotline)<br />\r\nEmail:&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:cr@visathingforstudent.com\">cr@visathingforstudent.com</a><br />\r\nWeb: www.visathingforstudent.com</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Consular services for foreign citizens&nbsp;by e-mail&nbsp;appointment&nbsp;only (<a href=\"mailto:newdelhi.cons@mae.ro\">newdelhi.cons@mae.ro</a>). The e-mail message should contain the following information:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Complete name of applicant;</li>\r\n	<li>Address including temporary address if the case;</li>\r\n	<li>Date and place of birth;</li>\r\n	<li>Personal identification number</li>\r\n	<li>Concise description of the situation and mention of the consular service required;</li>\r\n	<li>Proposal for two alternative appointments, date and time.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Romania Student Visa Fee:</strong><br />\r\n120 Euro</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Romania Student Visa Processing Time:</strong><br />\r\nIt usually takes 40 to 60 days after application submission to embassy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>&nbsp;Visa Check List</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>This is a basic checklist for Romania student visa from Bangladesh. Required documents depending on student&rsquo;s profile. VISAThing for Student provides you complete visa application assistance.&nbsp;</strong><strong>We provide information on Romania work permit, Romania tourist visa, student visa in Romania from Bangladesh, Romania student visa requirements, Romania&nbsp;student visa&nbsp;for&nbsp;Bangladeshi,romania student visa from Bangladesh, Romania embassy in Bangladesh.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Need help! connect with our expert&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"https://visathingforstudent.com/inquiry/\">visa consultant</a></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><strong>Passport:</strong>&nbsp;Original Passport with a validity of at least 12 months after the intended date of departure and minimum two blank pages for visa stamp. If you want passport, please&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"http://www.passport.gov.bd/\">click here.</a></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Visa Application Form:</strong>&nbsp;Completed and signed national visa application form</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Photo Specification:</strong>&nbsp;Color photograph (35mmx45mm) with white background</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Covering-Letter:</strong>&nbsp;Covering letter mentioning details of applicants, passport details, travel details and who will bear expenses details.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Confirmation of Enrolment:</strong>&nbsp;Original letter from the University or Recognized Educational Institution confirming admission and duration of the course.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Approval Letter:</strong>&nbsp;A copy of approval letter from Romanian Ministry of education.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Tuition Fees Payment Receipt:</strong>&nbsp;A payment receipt is a proof of payment that you have made payment to the institution.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Academic Documents:</strong>&nbsp;Please submit your all academic documents to Embassy/VAC</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Financial Means:</strong>&nbsp;Proof of financial means to cover the costs for the time of your studies.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Health Insurance:</strong>&nbsp;A proof of health insurance coverage whole period of study.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Birth Certificate:</strong>&nbsp;An original copy of Birth Registration Certificate. If you want Birth Registration Certificate please&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"http://bris.lgd.gov.bd/pub/application_form.aspx\">click here.</a></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Police Clearance:</strong>&nbsp;An original copy of Police Clearance Certificate. If you want Police Clearance Certificate please&nbsp;<strong><a href=\"http://pcc.police.gov.bd:8080/ords/f?p=500:1::::::\">click here.</a></strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Accommodation Details:</strong>&nbsp;Once you have confirmed where you will be studying, you must need to show accommodation details.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>Romania student visa requirements for Bangladeshi student</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>*** Further help, please contact with us through email or phone.</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Phone:&nbsp;</strong><strong>+88 01967777788</strong><strong>&nbsp;or Email:&nbsp;</strong><strong>cr@visathingforstudent.com</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>&nbsp;Visa Consultancy Fee</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Service&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Fee (BDT)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Consultancy&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 10,000/=</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>***15% VAT will be applicable on VISAThing for Student&rsquo;s service charge.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>&nbsp;Visa Application Charge</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Service&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Fee (BDT)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Submission&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;25,000/=</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>***15% VAT will be applicable on VISAThing for Student&rsquo;s service charge.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>&nbsp;Our Consultancy Services Include</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Creating checklist analyze your documents.</li>\r\n	<li>Identifying loop holes and eliminating those.</li>\r\n	<li>Screening your application in 3 stages.</li>\r\n	<li>Preparing best visa approach.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>&nbsp;for more information :&nbsp;https://visathingforstudent.com/countries/romania/</h2>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-23', 1),
(184, 'Russia', 'RUS', 'ru.png', '<p><strong>Study in Russia from Bangladesh:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Russia provides the most specialized education regarding technology or medical science along with commerce related subjects. Another positive aspect of Study in Russia is its fee structure which is reasonably lower than the course fee of other prominent countries. The medical and technical universities in Russia are counted among top 100 medical and technical universities of the world. The most prominent thing about Russia for a student is, it provides an opportunity of living along with world class tuition in lowest cost comparatively</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Entry Requirements:</strong><br />\r\nFor Bachelor: At least, 12 years of study have to be completed. Study gap of 3 years (Maximum) will be acceptable. ***(HSC result must not be below 4.00)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>For Masters:</strong> Bachelor or equivalent Degree completion. 3 years&rsquo; degree pass is also accepted. Partial result doesn&rsquo;t carry any extra significance to get admitted. Work experience is not required; but may carry extra gravity to secure admission in University.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Language Proficiency:</strong> No IELTS/ TOEFL are required</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Tuition Fees:</strong> All fees are subjected to the University and Subject selection made by the student. But perspective to the others country in the world Russia offers a very short range of tuition fees for the international student including accommodation cost.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Package:&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; BDT 2,50,000/=</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1st Payment: BDT 15,000/= (For application fees, courier charges, Original Invitation for Entry from the Federal Migration Service of the Russian)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Requirement for Russian Student Visa from Bangladesh:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Filled-in Visa Application Form with Questioner. Incomplete forms are NOT accepted. The form should be typed or written legibly.</li>\r\n	<li>A valid passport with an expiry date of 18 months into the future from the expected date of VISA issuance.</li>\r\n	<li>Birth Certificate Photocopy.</li>\r\n	<li>Original Invitation for Entry from the Federal Migration Service of the Russian</li>\r\n	<li>Original Air Tickets or Booking Confirmation receipt and their copies.</li>\r\n	<li>HIV Test (AIDS) Certificate and its copy as well as Medical Fitness Certificate and its copy in case if one applies for Visa with validity more than three months.</li>\r\n	<li>Copies of all Educational Certificates with detailed Subject and Grades description ****(Including BA/BSc/BBA and MA/MS/MSc certificates where applicable.) ****(Prospective Postgraduate students may be asked to Submit his/her &ldquo;Research Papers&rdquo;, if already done, or his/her &ldquo;Future Research Topic&rdquo; as per the instructions of the respective institute.</li>\r\n	<li>All the documents shall be translated into Russian, and attested by the Consular Department of the Embassy of the Russian federation in Dhaka.</li>\r\n	<li>One passport-size Photo of Applicant. The photo should be colored, preferably on matte paper.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Prospective Postgraduate students should graduate from their Alma Mater no more than 3 years prior to their admission date into a Russian Institute. Undergraduates and Doctorate candidates should not be no more than 21 years and 45 years respectively.<br />\r\nCandidates without Sufficient Russian Language proficiency, will be subjected to extra one-year Russian Language Program.<br />\r\nPaid Visa Fee. The Visa Fee depends upon the Type of Visa and is to be paid by Bank Draft against the Payment Order issued in the Consular Department, Embassy of Russian Federation. Dhaka. Bangladesh. Address: House NE(J) 9, Road 79<br />\r\nGulshan-2, Dhaka 1212</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Please call 01958-666999 &amp; 01958-666900 for more information.</p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2018-12-23', 1);
