(185, 'Rwanda', 'RWA', 'rw.png', '<h4>&nbsp;Basic information</h4>\r\n\r\n<h5>For Rwanda, VISAThing provides</h5>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>&nbsp;E-visa</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.visathing.com/visa-consultancy/\">Visa Consultancy</a></strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Rwanda visa for Bangladeshi ; Conference visa ; Visa Processing from Bangladesh ; Visa application ; Visa requirements for Bangladeshi citizen</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Rwanda does not have a diplomatic representation in People&rsquo;s Republic of Bangladesh. One can look for nearest Embassy of Rwanda which is in India.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you have all the below documents,&nbsp;<strong>VISAThing will provide you the E-visa support.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Rwanda issues Electronic Visa is popularly known as e-visa for various categories of visa for Bangladeshi nationals willing to travel for a short-term visit. Rwanda e-visa is issued as a conditional authorization granted by the central Immigration authority to a foreigner to enter the territory, remain within, or to leave the territory before the validity of the authorization expires.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Rwanda e-visa allows an applicant to apply online with scanned copies of very few documents, get the visa processed within a very short time and get the visa online in the form of PDF/Doc file over email. Though Rwanda e-visa is a valid visa permit, it doesn&rsquo;t guarantee the right to enter the territory of Rwanda. The immigration authority reserves the right to grant the final permission of entry.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>&nbsp;Fees &amp; Processing Time</h4>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>VISA PROCESSING FEE</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" style=\"width:917px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;Visa Type</td>\r\n			<td>Visa &amp; Application Fee (BDT)</td>\r\n			<td>Logistics charge (BDT)</td>\r\n			<td>Total (BDT)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><strong>Single Entry</strong></td>\r\n			<td>5625/-</td>\r\n			<td>25000/-</td>\r\n			<td><strong>30625/-</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><strong>Multiple Entry</strong></td>\r\n			<td>5625/-</td>\r\n			<td>25000/-</td>\r\n			<td><strong>30625/-</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Processing Time:</strong>&nbsp;Total approximate time is 10 to 12 working days (3-5 working days at Embassy&nbsp;<strong>+&nbsp;</strong>7 working days for Passport transit).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>** 15% VAT is applicable on VISAThing&rsquo;s service (logistic) charge.</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<h4>&nbsp;Consultancy</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Our Premium Visa Consultancy for Over 86 Countries in the World is a 360 degree approach. It enables you to prepare your visa application perfectly according to your profile. Proper visa documentation depends on several factors. Hence, we conduct a complete background and travel history check on the client. Based on that, accurate customized consultation is provided. Clients are carefully explained the specific documents&rsquo; requirements for visa application to improve its acceptability. Under this hood, we do all the pre-application document screening on your behalf. We provide visa support for over 70 countries which doesn&rsquo;t have Embassy presence in Bangladesh, to free you from any recurring hassles.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We will open up a case file under your name and details to analyze your travel and professional history. Then, we will prepare the best possible approach for a successful visa application. You can only avail our Visa Consultancy Support upon purchase of the service and once you have agreed to our terms &amp; conditions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Please call our hotline numbers to book your consultancy slot.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Our consultancy services include:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>1 . Studying Your Background &amp; Travel History,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2 . Creating Checklist based on Profile Merit.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3 . Identifying Loop Holes and Eliminating those,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4 . Preparing Best Visa Application Approach.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Tele-Consultancy Services for Distant Clients:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you&rsquo;re not able to reach us in person, you can still take our Consultancy support. We can arrange Audio/Video Consultancy at your preferred time over Skype/What&rsquo;sApp or any convenient application. Please email us for details &amp; call for appointment (Sunday to Thursday).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Call for Your Appointment:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>0196 777 7788 (Hotline) or E-mail us: cr@visathing.com</p>\r\n\r\n<p>*** Our Consultancy fee starts from BDT 10,000/- up to 50,000/- per Applicant (Based on country, visa category &amp; the complexity of case). At first, we will listen to your case and finalize the Consultancy Fee. Then, at the time of opening your case file you need to make the payment and afterwards we will sit for the Detail Consultation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Please Note:</strong>&nbsp;Our Consultancy Fee is excluding Logistics Fee, Visa Fee, VFS Fee, Translation &amp; Notary, Asset Declaration, Travel Insurance and/or other related charges. Our service is to properly guide you to prepare your visa application documents both in verbal &amp; written forms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>&nbsp;Check List</h2>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>VISA REQUIREMENTS FOR DIPLOMATIC/OFFICIAL PASSPORT HOLDER:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>1. Passport:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Original Passport with validity of minimum six months after the intended date of departure and minimum two blank pages for visa stamp.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Include all your previous passports.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>2. Visa Application Form:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Two visa application forms duly filled and signed. Photocopy can be used.&nbsp;<strong><u>Click here to download visa form.</u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>3. Photo:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Three recent passport size photographs,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With matt&nbsp;or semi matt&nbsp;finish,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Photographs should be white background, without border,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>60-80% face coverage, (Size: 3.5 cm X 4.5 cm).</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>4. Covering-Letter:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Covering Letter from applicant including Name, Designation, Passport Number, purpose and&nbsp;&nbsp; outlining who will be responsible for the full costs of the trip &ndash; travel, accommodation, expenses etc. The letter should be addressed to &ndash; The Visa Officer, Rwanda High Commission, New Delhi. Visa Category must be mentioned in the subject line (Recommended)</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>5. Invitation Letter:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>An invitation letter from the host / inviting Company in Rwanda on its letter head stating the purpose of travel and duration of stay and should be duly signed with signatory&rsquo;s name, designation and seal.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>6. Government Order:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>This letter, commonly called the GO Letter works as a forwarding letter for government officials/service holders. It is issued from the respective government office where the visa applicant is stationed. GO Letter is duly signed and stamped according to the standard format set by government offices detailing applicant&rsquo;s basic information, purpose of visit, statement on undertakings of responsibilities/funding etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>7. Note Verbal:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>This letter is basically issued as a visa support letter issued from the Ministry of Foreign Affairs according to the standard format set by ministry detailing applicant&rsquo;s basic information, purpose of visit, duration of the trip etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>8. Financials:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Original copy of Bank Statement (salary)/ Personal bank statement for last 6 months&nbsp;&nbsp; mentioning the Bank&rsquo;s name, Bank&rsquo;s Telephone Number clearly with authorized bank seal and signature (e-statement is not acceptable)</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>9. Ticket:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Ticket Itinerary as per your travel period.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>10. Hotel Reservation:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Hotel booking as per your travel period.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>11. Medical:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Yellow fever certificate.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>BUSINESS VISA REQUIREMENTS:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>1. Passport:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Original Passport with validity of minimum six months after the intended date of departure and minimum two blank pages for visa stamp.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Include all your previous passports.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>2. Visa Application Form:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Two visa application forms duly filled and signed. Photocopy can be used.&nbsp;<strong><u>Click here to download visa form.</u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>3. Photo:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Three recent passport size photographs,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With matt&nbsp;or semi matt&nbsp;finish,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Photographs should be white background, without border,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>60-80% face coverage, (Size: 3.5 cm X 4.5 cm)</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>4. Covering-Letter:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Covering Letter from applicant including Name, Designation, Passport Number, purpose and outlining who will be responsible for the full costs of the trip &ndash; travel, accommodation, expenses etc. The letter should be addressed to &ndash; The Visa Officer, Rwanda High Commission, New Delhi. Visa Category must be mentioned in the subject line.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>5. Invitation Letter:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>An invitation letter from the host / inviting Company in Rwanda on its letter head stating the purpose of travel and duration of stay and should be duly signed with signatory&rsquo;s name, designation and seal.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>6. Proof of Occupation:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Forwarding-Letter: A letter from the office such a NOC/LOI letter on the organization&rsquo;s letter-head pad stating applicant&rsquo;s name, designation, passport number, purpose, duration of visit, sponsorship status etc. Addressing to- The Visa Officer, Rwanda High Commission, New Delhi.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Trade license/Certificate of Incorporation/Memorandum (If self-employed/businessman)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Office ID card copy/ Visiting card (3 copies)</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>7. Financials:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Original copy of Bank Statement (salary)/ Personal bank statement for last 6 months mentioning the Bank&rsquo;s name, Bank&rsquo;s Telephone Number clearly with authorized bank seal and signature (e-statement is not acceptable)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Employer Company&rsquo;s Bank Statement for last 6 months mentioning the Bank&rsquo;s name, Bank&rsquo;s Telephone Number clearly. (If the trip is sponsored by the employer)</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>8. Ticket:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Ticket Itinerary as per your travel period.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>9. Hotel Reservation:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Hotel booking as per your travel period.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>10. Medical:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Yellow fever certificate.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>TOURIST VISA REQUIREMENT:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>1. Passport:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Original Passport with validity of minimum six months after the intended date of departure and minimum two blank pages for visa stamp.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Include all your previous passports</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>2. Visa Application Form:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Two visa application forms duly filled and signed. Photocopy can be used.&nbsp;<strong><u>Click here to download visa form.</u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>3. Photo:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Three recent passport size photographs,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With matt&nbsp;or semi matt&nbsp;finish,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Photographs should be white background, without border,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>60-80% face cove