(206, 'Somalia', 'SOM', 'so.png', '<h1>Somalia Visa from Bangladesh<br />\r\n<a href=\"https://visathing.com/continent/africa/\" rel=\"tag\">Africa</a></h1>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>&nbsp;Visa Consultancy</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bangladeshi nationals can obtain a visa on arrival for a maximum stay of 30 days.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>&nbsp;Check List</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>A traveler must have following documents:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>1.&nbsp; Passport</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>A passport valid for the duration of stay is required.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>2. Invitation letter</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>An invitation letter issued and provided by the sponsor must be submitted to the Airport Immigration Department at least 2 days before arrival.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>3. Visa Fee:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Visa fee is USD 50. Extension of stay is possible for additional 30 days.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>4. Compulsory Currency Exchange:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Upon arrival all visitors must exchange USD 100, or equivalent of other freely convertible foreign currencies into local currency;&nbsp;exemption for children under 18 years of age.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:22px\">for more information :&nbsp;https://visathing.com/country/somalia/</span></p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-25', 1),
