(228, 'Tunisia', 'TUN', 'tn.png', '<h4>&nbsp;</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>&nbsp;Fees &amp; Processing Time</h4>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>VISA PROCESSING FEE</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" style=\"width:915px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;Number of Entry</td>\r\n			<td>Application Center Fee (BDT)</td>\r\n			<td>Logistics charge (BDT)</td>\r\n			<td>Total (BDT)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><strong>Single</strong></td>\r\n			<td>5,700/-</td>\r\n			<td>25000/-</td>\r\n			<td><strong>30,700/-</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;Multiple</td>\r\n			<td>5,700/-</td>\r\n			<td>25000/-</td>\r\n			<td><strong>30,700/-</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>** 15% VAT is applicable on VISAThing&rsquo;s service (logistic) charge.</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>PROCESSING TIME</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Total approximate time is 17 to 19 working days (10-12 working days&nbsp;(both for tourist &amp; business) at Embassy&nbsp;<strong>+&nbsp;</strong>7 working days for Passport transit).</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>&nbsp;Consultancy</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Our Premium Visa Consultancy for Over 86 Countries in the World is a 360-degree approach. It enables you to prepare your visa application perfectly according to your profile. Proper visa documentation depends on several factors.&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.visathing.com/visa-consultancy/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">&hellip;Read more</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>&nbsp;Check List</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>TOURIST VISA REQUIREMENTS</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>1. Passport:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Original Passport with validity of minimum six months from the date of travel and minimum two blank pages for visa stamp.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Copy of Passport</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Attach all your old passports (if any)</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>2. Tunisia Visa Application Form:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>One visa application form duly filled and signed.<a href=\"https://www.visathing.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Tunisia.pdf\"><strong>&nbsp;Click Here to Download</strong></a></p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>3. Photo Specification:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Two recent passport size photographs with matt or semi-matt finish, 60% &ndash; 80% face coverage, light background and without border (Size: 35mm x 45mm).<br />\r\nPlease note: Photograph should not be more than 3 months old, scanned/stapled and should not be used in any of the previous visas.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>4. Forwarding Letter:&nbsp;</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>A Forwarding Letter from the applicant (Plain paper) duly stamped &amp; seal, stating applicant&rsquo;s name, designation, passport number, purpose and duration of visit duly signed by an authorized signatory. The letter should be addressed to The Visa Officer, Embassy of the Republic of Tunisia, New Delhi.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>5. Financial:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Bank statement for the last six months with bank seal and stamp.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>6. Ticket:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Confirmed Roundtrip Air Ticket</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Please Note:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Copy of certified identity document with applicant&rsquo;s photo. (ID card or Driver license)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. The application should be submitted before ten days of departure.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. One set copy of all documents is required.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. All the documents including passport copy are needed to be scanned &amp; sent through E-mail (<a href=\"mailto:tunisiaembassy@airtelmail.in\">tunisiaembassy@airtelmail.in</a>) to the embassy&nbsp;<strong>(in one PDF file and has to be within 3MB)</strong>and once embassy will receive the same, the documents can be submitted physically in the embassy for visa processing. It is advisable that e-mail is done a day prior to the date of submission.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>BUSINESS VISA REQUIREMENT</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>1. Passport:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Original Passport with validity of minimum six months from the date of travel and minimum two blank pages for visa stamp.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Copy of Passport</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Attach all your old passports (if any)</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>2. Tunisia Visa Application Form:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>One visa application form duly filled and signed.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>3. Photo Specification</strong>:</h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Two recent passport size photographs with matt or semi-matt finish, 60%-80% face coverage, light background and without border (Size: 35mm x 45mm).<br />\r\nPlease note: Photograph should not be more than 3 months old, scanned/stapled and should not be used in any of the previous visas.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>4. Covering-Letter:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Covering Letter from the applicant (Plain paper) duly stamped &amp; seal, stating the applicant&rsquo;s name, designation, passport number, purpose and duration of visit duly signed by an authorized signatory. The letter should be addressed to: The Visa Officer, Embassy of the Republic of Tunisia, New Delhi.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>5. Forwarding-Letter:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Forwarding Letter/NOC from the applicant on company&rsquo;s letterhead mentioning the name, designation, passport number, purpose of visit and duration of the visit. The letter should be addressed to: The Visa Officer, Embassy of the Republic of Tunisia, New Delhi.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>6. Invitation Letter:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Invitation Letter from Tunisia host / Inviting Company on its letterhead stating the purpose of visit and duration of travel, duly attested by Municipal Corporation in Tunisia. The letter should be faxed directly to the embassy and a copy to us.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Recommendation Letter through recognized Chamber of Commerce in Bangladesh.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>7. Financial:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Bank statement for the last six months with bank seal and stamp.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5><strong>8. Ticket:</strong></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>Confirmed Round-trip Air Ticket.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Please Note:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. Copy of certified identity document with applicant&rsquo;s photo. (ID card or Driver license)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. The application should be submitted before ten days of departure.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. One set copy of all documents is required.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. All the documents including passport copy need to be scanned &amp; send through E-mail (<a href=\"mailto:tunisiaembassy@airtelmail.in\">tunisiaembassy@airtelmail.in</a>) to the embassy&nbsp;<strong>(in one PDF file and has to be within 3MB)</strong>and once embassy will receive the same, the documents can be submitted physically in the embassy for visa processing. It is advisable that e-mail is done a day prior to the date of submission.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:24px\">for more information :&nbsp;https://visathing.com/country/tunisia/</span></p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-25', 1),
(229, 'Turkey', 'TUR', 'tr.png', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>DOCUMENTS REQUIRED FOR TURKISH STUDENT VISA</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">2 Biometric photos at 5X7 cm with white background</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Orignal passport with color photocopy</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Orignal identity document (Tazkira) with color photocopy</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Financial guarantor&rsquo;s proof of income which covers last 3 months Bank statement, Manimum balance should be USD 15000 $.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Travel insurance</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Acceptance letter of one of the educational institution for the bachelor, Master degree and Ph.D.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">The university or educational institution is obligated to email the acceptance letter to Turkish Consulate General in Mazar-e-Sharif Afghanistan</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Original certificate, Diploma and transcript with copies, which is attested by Ministry of foreign affairs of the Islamic republic of Afghanistan.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">Financial guarantor&rsquo;s letter for applicant stating he/she covers the entire cost during education</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">If the student&rsquo;s age is less than 18 years, it is necessary that the parents of the student should visit to the consulate and receive a standard agreement.</li>\r\n	<li style=\"text-align: justify;\">If the applicant is resident of the region not covered by Turkish Consulate General in Mazar-e-Sharif Afghanistan, applicant must bring resident confirmation letter from local municipality.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Note: I</strong>f necessary, the applicant is required to attend the meeting in Turkish Consulate General in Mazar-e-Sharif Afghanistan. The process may take one to two months.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Indoor facilities: Travel Insurance, Photography, Photocopy, Ticket Reservation, Hotel Reservation</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>Visa fee:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Single Entry : USD 60</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Multiple Entry : USD 200</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><strong>TVAC Service Charges:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Normal Lounge Service : USD 20 per applicant.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">Business Lounge Service (with prior appointment) : USD 50 per applicant.</p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2018-10-22', 1),
