(242, 'Vanuatu', 'VUT', 'vu.png', '<h4>&nbsp;Basic information</h4>\r\n\r\n<h1>Vanuatu Visa from Bangladesh<br />\r\n<a href=\"https://visathing.com/continent/oceania/\" rel=\"tag\">Oceania</a></h1>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Vanuatu visa is on arrival for Bangladeshi Nationals. There is no Embassy or High Commission of Vanuatu in Bangladesh, the nearest consular office is in New Delhi, India. However, they do not issue any sticker visa or any OTB (Ok To Board) Certificate for Bangladeshi Nationals. So, an applicant is advised to get on arrival visa for 30 days. The following documents are required to show in the immigration:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Passports and/or passport replacing documents must be valid.</li>\r\n	<li>Visitors are required to hold proof of sufficient funds to cover their stay and documents required for their next destination.</li>\r\n	<li>Visitors must need to hold return/onward tickets.</li>\r\n	<li>Visitors applying for a visa on arrival must hold a proof of purpose of stay, return/onward ticket and at least 500 USD or equivalent in cash/credit card.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:22px\">for more information please ckick here :&nbsp;https://visathing.com/country/vanuatu/</span></p>\r\n', '2018-09-11', '2021-02-28', 1),
